Dr. Everett Shapiro ( 1917-January 1 , 2002 ) was an American Orthodontist who was past President of American Board of Orthodontics and American Journal of Orthodontics and Dentofacial Orthopedics .
David Nachmansohn ( 17 March 1899 -- 2 November 1983 ) was a German - Jewish biochemist responsible for elucidating the role of phosphocreatine in energy production in the muscles , and the role of the neurotransmitter acetylcholine in nerve stimulation .
Luis María Peralta ( 1759 in Sonora , New Spain -- August 26 , 1851 ) was a soldier in the Spanish Army , who received one of the largest of the Spanish land grants , Rancho San Antonio , a 44,800-acre ( 181 km2 ) plot that encompassed most of the East Bay region of California .
Laban Moiben ( born 13 October 1983 ) is a Kenyan long - distance runner who competes professionally in marathon races .

Ulla Johanna Caroline Grane ( born 19 April 1978 in Stockholm ) is a Swedish realtor who works in New York , United States .
Sola Olorunfemi ( born 6 June 1967 ) is a Nigerian economist and a statistician .
Johann Paul Schiffelholz ( 13 March 1685 -- 28 January 1758 ) , was a German Baroque composer and an important composer for the variety of baroque lute called colascione , as well as writing the usual trio sonatas , etc . , for the violin family of instruments .
Edward Gamblin ( 1948 -- 2010 ) was a Canadian country rock singer and songwriter , who was one of the most influential early stars of First Nations music .
Thomas de Barry ( fl . 1560 ) , was canon of Glasgow , and chief magistrate of Bothwell .
Col . Dewitt Clinton Haskin ( circa 1824 -- July 17 , 1900 ) was an American engineer whose developed the initial methods for construction of the first tunnels under the Hudson River between New Jersey and Manhattan .
Aleksei Andreyevich Volkov ( 1859 - -1929 ) was a valet at the court of Tsar Nicholas II . He escaped a death march at Perm in September 1918 and survived to write his memoirs about his time at court and his escape .
Paul Fonoroff ( born 1954 in Cleveland , Ohio ) is one of Hong Kong 's best known film critics and film historians .
Zhu Jin ( 朱瑾 ) ( 867 - 918 ) was a warlord late in the Chinese dynasty Tang Dynasty who would later be a major general of the Wu ( also known as Hongnong ) state during the subsequent Five Dynasties and Ten Kingdoms period .
Heinrich Jacob Bashuysen ( October 26 , 1679 -- c. 1750 ) was a German Christian printer of Hebrew books and Orientalist .
Stephan Kunzelmann ( born 22 November 1978 ) is a retired German freestyle swimmer who won three medals in the 4×100 m freestyle relay at the 2000 FINA World Swimming Championships ( 25 m ) and 2000 and 2002 European Aquatics Championships .
John Baskcomb ( 7 February 1916 -- 29 March 2000 ) was an English character actor who made numerous television and film appearances over a 35-year period .
Carol Bergé ( 1928 - -2006 ) was an American poet , highly active in the literary , performing and visual arts renaissance of the 1960s and 1970s in New York City .
Ryan Hemsworth ( born 1990 ) is a Canadian record producer and DJ . Raised in Halifax , Nova Scotia , he attended University of King 's College , where he studied journalism .
Vladimir Galkin ( born 30 June 1954 , in Kazan , Russia ) is a chemist , the Dean of the chemistry department of Kazan State University and the director of Butlerov Institute .

Isamu Fujisawa ( born 12 October 1987 ) is a Japanese racewalker .
Stephen Deblois ( 1699 - -1778 ) was a musician who lived in New York and Boston , Massachusetts in the 18th century .

Chuvanna Vithukal ( English : Red Seedlings ) is a 1978 Indian Malayalam socio - political film , directed by P. A. Backer and produced by Salam Karassery .
Ginger Ale Afternoon is a 1989 independent film by director Rafal Zielinski , based on a stage play by Gina Wendkos .
Orwell Rolls in His Grave is a 2003 American documentary film directed by Robert Kane Pappas and written by Pappas and Tom Blackburn .
Bhoomiyude Avakashikal ( English : The Inheritors of the Earth ) is a 2012 Malayalam feature film written and directed by T. V. Chandran .

Miss Mink of 1949 is a 1949 American comedy film directed by Glenn Tryon ( his last film as a director ) and written by Arnold Belgard .
Vijayanagarada Veeraputhra ( Kannada : ವಿಜಯನಗರದ ವೀರಪುತ್ರ ) is a 1961 Indian Kannada film , directed by R. Nagendra Rao and produced by R Nagendra Rao .
The One Who Will Stay Unnoticed ( Croatian : Onaj koji će ostati neprimijećen ) is a Croatian drama film directed by Zvonimir Jurić .
Oru Sumangaliyude Katha is a 1984 Indian Malayalam film , directed by Baby , story written by Oscar Movies M Bhaskar and produced by S Kumar .
American Heist is a 2014 American independent action film directed by Armenian director Sarik Andreasyan , based on the 1959 film The Great St. Louis Bank Robbery directed by Charles Guggenheim and John Stix .
Captain Scarlett is a 1953 American Techinicolor swashbuckler film directed by Thomas Carr , that was shot in Mexico .
November 1828 is a 1979 Indonesian historical drama directed by Teguh Karya .
Lady Stay Dead is a 1981 Australian thriller film directed by Terry Bourke about a psychotic handyman .
Made by Walter Wanger Productions and Universal International Pictures , it was directed by George Marshall and produced by Walter Wanger from a screenplay by Alan Le May , based on the 1942 novel Tap Roots by James H. Street , with additional dialogue by Lionel Wiggam .

KL Gangster is a 2011 Malaysian action film written and directed by Syamsul Yusof , ( who also starred in the film ) .
Panama Pasama ( English : Money or Affection ) is a 1968 Indian Tamil film , directed and produced by K. S. Gopalakrishnan .
Song of the Miraculous Hind ( Hungarian : Ének a csodaszarvasról ) is a 2002 Hungarian animated mythological and historical film directed by Marcell Jankovics .
Urbanized is a documentary film directed by Gary Hustwit and released on 26 October 2011 and considered the third of a three - part series on design known as the Design Trilogy , the first being Helvetica about the typeface and the second being Objectified about industrial design .
Abgehauen is a 1998 German television documentary directed by Frank Beyer and based on the autobiographical book of the same name by Manfred Krug .
Serangan Fajar ( released internationally as Attack at Dawn ) is a 1982 Indonesian war film directed by Arifin C. Noer and produced by G. Dwipayana .
Dead Woman from Beverly Hills ( German : Die Tote von Beverly Hills ) is a 1964 West German drama film directed by Michael Pfleghar .
Erivansky Uyezd ( Russian : Эриванский уезд ) was one of the uyezds ( administrative units ) of Erivan Governorate of the Russian Empire with its center in Erivan from 1846 until its formal abolition in 1917 .

Bavaria - Munich ( German : Bayern - München ) was a duchy which was part of the Holy Roman Empire from 1392 to 1505 .

Torill Selsvold Nyborg ( born 23 February 1952 ) is a Norwegian nurse , missionary and politician for the Christian Democratic Party .

Phoebe Hessel , née Smith ( March 1713 -- 12 December 1821 ) was best known for disguising herself as a man to serve in the British Army , probably to be with her lover , Samuel Golding .

James Campbell Clouston ( 31 August 1900 -- 3 June 1940 ) was a Canadian officer of the British Royal Navy , who acted as pier - master during the Dunkirk evacuation , and who was lost when his motor launch was sunk by enemy aircraft .

Ted H. Scroggins was born in Tahlequah , Oklahoma , on 13 September 1918 and enlisted in the United States Navy on 7 December 1939 .

Prince Carl Christian of Hohenzollern ( German : Carl Christian Friedrich Johannes Meinrad Maria Hubertus Edmund Prinz von Hohenzollern ) ( born 5 April 1962 ) is the eldest child of Prince Johann Georg of Hohenzollern and of his wife Princess Birgitta of Sweden , sister of King Carl XVI Gustaf of Sweden .

The Mornos empties into the Gulf of Corinth about 3 km southeast of Nafpaktos .
The Blees is a river flowing through Luxembourg , joining the Sauer at Bleesbruck .
Formed by the confluence of the Bedford and Glen Erskine creeks , the Erskine Creek ( officially designated a river ) rises below Mount Erskine , between Bullaburra and Wentworth Falls , and flows generally south , north - east , and east , before reaching its confluence with the Nepean River , near Mulgoa .
The Kabul River ( Persian / Urdu : دریای کابل‎ ; Pashto : کابل سیند‎ , Sanskrit : कुभा ) , the classical Cophes /ˈkoʊfiːz/ , is a 700-kilometre ( 430 mi ) long river that emerges in the Sanglakh Range of the Hindu Kush mountains in Afghanistan and empties into the Indus River near Attock , Pakistan .
As one of the few designated safe harbours on the city side of the bay , the Patterson River is the most popular boating gateway to Port Phillip Bay .
The Llano River ( /ˈlænoʊ/ LAN - oh ) is a tributary of the Colorado River , approximately 105 miles ( 169 km ) long , in central Texas in the United States .
The Ennepe is a river and a left tributary of the Volme in Northern Sauerland , Germany .
Oban River rises below Mount Duncan , Great Dividing Range on the slopes of the Great Dividing Range , within Little Llangothlin Lake , north of Guyra , and flows generally north - east towards its confluence with the Sara River , within Guy Fawkes River National Park and Chaelundi National Park .
The Tungabhadra River is a river in southern India that starts and flows through the state of Karnataka during most of its course , before flowing along the border between Karnataka and Andhra Pradesh and ultimately joining the Krishna River along the border of Andhra Pradesh and Telangana .
Nambucca River rises below Killiekrankie Mountain on the Dorrigo Plateau , part of the Great Dividing Range , and flows generally east southeast , joined by four tributaries including Taylors Arm , before reaching its mouth at the Tasman Sea of the South Pacific Ocean , at Nambucca Heads .
The Sangha River , a tributary of the Congo River , is located in Central Africa .
The Pelotas River ( Portuguese , Rio Pelotas ) ( Portuguese pronunciation : ( peˈlɔtɐs ) ) is a river in southern Brazil , and a tributary of the Uruguay River .
Part of the Po basin , it is a left tributary of the Dora Riparia and forms the valley called the Val Cenischia which marks the boundary between the Graian Alps to the north and the Cottian Alps to the south .

The Ille ( French pronunciation : ​(il ) ) is a small river in Brittany , France , right tributary of the river Vilaine .
The Oglio ( Italian : ( ˈɔʎʎo ) ; Latin Ollius , or Olius ; Lombard Òi ) is a left - side tributary of the Po River in Lombardy , Italy .
Tatarka River ( Russian : Татарка ) is a river in Perm Krai , Russia , a right bank tributary of the Babka River , which in turn is a tributary of the Sylva River .
The Chuya River ( Russian : Чуя ) is a river in the Altai Republic in Russia , a right tributary of the Katun River ( Ob 's basin ) .
The Luama River is a tributary of the Lualaba River in the Democratic Republic of the Congo ( DRC ) .
The Huveaune rises in the Castelette cave at 590 metres ( 1,940 ft ) in the Sainte - Baume mountain range , and discharges into the Mediterranean Sea at Marseille .
The Adar River ( or Khor Adar ) , known to the Dinka as the Yal , is a tributary of the White Nile in the state of Upper Nile , South Sudan .
Bilgola Creek rises about 1 kilometre ( 0.62 mi ) west of Bilgola Head and flows generally east by south , from the Bilgola Escarpment through Littoral rainforest , coastal woodland and coastal clay heath communities directly out onto Bilgola Beach and into the Tasman Sea .
The Nattai River rises on the Mittagong Range within the Great Dividing Range , south of Mittagong , and flows generally north northwest and then north northeast , joined by nine tributaries including the Little River , before reaching its confluence with the Wollondilly River within Lake Burragorang southwest of the locality of Nattai .
The Birim River is one of the main tributaries of the Pra River in Ghana and the country 's most important diamond - producing area , flowing through most of the width of the Eastern region .
Walcrow River rises within the Tia Range on the eastern slopes of the Great Dividing Range , below Mount Carrington , south southeast of Walcha and flows generally southeast by south , before reaching its confluence with the Cooplacurripa River , north of Giro , northwest of Taree .
The Drwęca ( ˈdrvɛnt͡sa ) ( German : Drewenz , Lithuanian : Druvinčia ) is a river in northern Poland and a tributary of the Vistula river near Toruń , forming a part of the city 's administrative boundary .
The Jagst ( German pronunciation : ( ˈjakst ) ) is a right tributary of the Neckar in northern Baden - Württemberg .
The Higgs boson is named after Peter Higgs , one of six physicists who , in 1964 , proposed the mechanism that suggested the existence of such a particle .
The name `` Nicaragua '' was coined by Spanish colonists based on the name `` Nicarao '' , chief of the most populous indigenous tribe .
Helix Producer 1 is a ship - shaped monohull floating production and offloading vessel , converted from the ferry MV Karl Carstens .
In mathematics , the Cauchy condensation test , named after Augustin - Louis Cauchy , is a standard convergence test for infinite series .
Lutheranism is a major branch of Protestant Christianity that identifies with the theology of Martin Luther ( 1483 - 1546 ) -- a German friar , ecclesiastical reformer and theologian .
Ullmannite was named for German chemist and mineralogist , Johann Christoph Ullmann ( 1771 - -1821 ) , one of the fathers of systematic mineralogy .
The name of the town , `` Al - Malikiyah '' , is named after a Syrian army officer Adnan al - Malki .
Thórsmörk ( Icelandic : Þórsmörk , ( listen ) ) is a mountain ridge in Iceland that was named after the Norse god Thor ( Þórr ) .
Festa Junina ( Portuguese pronunciation : ( ˈfɛstɐ ʒuˈnĩnɐ ) , June Festival ) , also known as festa de São João for their part in celebrating the nativity of St. John the Baptist , are the annual Brazilian celebrations historically related to European Midsummer that take place in the beginning of the Brazilian winter .
The Museu d'Art Jaume Morera ( Jaume Morera Art Museum ) is a museum in Lleida ( Catalonia ) created by the Diputació de Lleida and the Lleida City Council ( La Paeria ) with the collaboration of the painter Jaume Morera i Galícia .
In mathematics , the Poincaré duality theorem , named after Henri Poincaré , is a basic result on the structure of the homology and cohomology groups of manifolds .
The Cannizzaro reaction , named after its discoverer Stanislao Cannizzaro , is a chemical reaction that involves the base - induced disproportionation of an aldehyde lacking a hydrogen atom in the alpha position .
Igbo art ( Igbo : Ǹkà Igbo ) is any body of visual art originating from the Igbo people .
The Görres Society was founded on 25 January 1876 in Koblenz by Catholic scientists and writers as the Görres - Gesellschaft zur Pflege der katholischen Wissenschaften in honour of Joseph Görres to advance Roman Catholic studies .
Lister Cars is a British sports car manufacturer founded by Brian Lister in 1954 in Cambridge , England , which became known for its involvement in motorsport .
Hall Basin is named after American polar explorer Charles Francis Hall .
The 9K111 Fagot ( Russian : 9K111 `` Фагот '' ; English meaning of the word : `` bassoon '' ) is a second - generation tube - launched SACLOS wire - guided anti - tank missile system of the Soviet Union for use from ground or vehicle mounts .
Kleetopes are named after Victor Klee .
7529 Vagnozzi ( 1994 BC ) is a main - belt asteroid , whose name is dedicated to Antonio Vagnozzi , an amateur Italian astronomer , a prolific discoverer of asteroids at Santa Lucia Stroncone Astronomical Observatory in Stroncone , Italy .
In mathematics , the syzygetic pencil or Hesse pencil , named for Otto Hesse , is a pencil ( one - dimensional family ) of cubic plane elliptic curves in the complex projective plane , defined by the equation \lambda(x^3+y^3+z^3 ) + \mu xyz = 0 .

Goethite ( FeO(OH ) ) , ( /ˈɡɜrtaɪt/ GUR - tite ) named after the German polymath and poet Johann Wolfgang von Goethe ( 1749 - -1832 ) , an iron bearing hydroxide mineral of the diaspore group , is found in soil and other low - temperature environments .
Siouxland is a vernacular region that encompasses the entire Big Sioux River drainage basin in the U.S. states of South Dakota , Minnesota , Nebraska and Iowa .
Riddarholmsbron ( Swedish : `` The Knights Islet bridge '' ) is a bridge in Gamla stan , the old town in central Stockholm , Sweden , leading from the square Riddarhustorget on Stadsholmen to the smaller neighbouring island Riddarholmen .
Varignon 's theorem is a statement in Euclidean geometry by Pierre Varignon that was first published in 1731 .
In mathematics , a Fermat number , named after Pierre de Fermat who first studied them , is a positive integer of the form F--(n ) = 2^((2^n ) ) + 1 where n is a nonnegative integer .
In 1844 , Joseph Liouville showed that all Liouville numbers are transcendental , thus establishing the existence of transcendental numbers for the first time .
Chlorargyrite is the mineral form of silver chloride ( AgCl ) .
The Rheinpark ( meaning : Rhine park ) is a 40 hectare ( 0,4 km² ) large urban park along the right bank of the River Rhine in Cologne , Germany .

Janele Hyer - Spencer began her career as an activist , advocate , lawyer and politician on the foundation of devotion to family and the values of hard work .

Ty Longley ( September 4 , 1971 -- February 20 , 2003 ) was an American guitarist and vocalist .
Albert Tipton ( March 16 , 1917 -- October 5 , 1997 ) was an American flutist , pianist and conductor .

Connie Eaton ( March 1 , 1950 -- September 30 , 1999 ) was a country music singer .

Chipps Chippendale ( real name William Henry James Chippendale III ) is a mountain biking journalist in the UK .
Volker Strassen ( born April 29 , 1936 ) is a German mathematician , a professor emeritus in the department of mathematics and statistics at the University of Konstanz .
Elizabeth Rebecca Edwin was the daughter of actor William Talbot Richards ( d. 1813 ) , who at the time of her birth in Dublin had been engaged with her mother at the Crow Street Theatre .

Pauline Prior - Pitt is a British poet who lives in North Uist , Scotland .
Adeline Trafton Knox ( abt . 1842 - -1920 ? ) was an American writer and novelist , she published most of her work in the 1870s .
Lieutenant General John B. Conaway ( born August 23 , 1934 ) is a retired U.S. Air Force officer who served as the Chief of the National Guard Bureau in Washington , D.C. from 1990 to 1993 .
Ady Spencer born in Warrington , Cheshire , England is a former professional rugby league player .
Tomasz Gudzowaty ( born 1971 ) is a Polish documentary , portrait and art photographer , who gained international recognition through numerous publications and awards , most notably -- in World Press Photo in which he succeeded nine times .
Todd Glickman ( born June 13 , 1956 ) is a meteorologist whose weather reports can be heard on WCBS Newsradio-880 in New York City and internationally at cbsnewyork.com .
Mary Edwards Wertsch ( born Mary Brightwell Edwards on July 23 , 1951 ) is an author , journalist , independent publisher and expert on the subculture of American military brats .
John Gebhard ( February 22 , 1782 Claverack , Columbia County , New York -- January 3 , 1854 Schoharie , Schoharie County , New York ) was an American lawyer and politician from New York .

Jeffrey Alan Schechter ( usually credited as Jeff Schechter ) is a screenwriter whose work has been nominated for two Emmy awards , a Writers Guild of America award , and a Writers Guild of Canada award .
Jason Bellini ( born July 12 , 1975 ) is an American journalist , and until August 2008 was the lead news anchor for CBS News on Logo .
Robert Beauchamp ( 1923 -- March 1995 ) was an American figurative painter and arts educator .
Gurney Norman is an American writer , documentarian , and professor .
Andrea Mágori or Mrs. József Mágori ( née Balogi ; born May 1 , 1952 ) is a Hungarian politician , member of the National Assembly ( MP ) for Makó ( Csongrád County Constituency VII ) from 2010 to 2014 .
Wolf Kahn ( born October 4 , 1927 ) is a German - born American painter .
Robert E. Lane is an American political scientist and political psychologist .
Dr. Maurice Macdonald Seymour M.D. , C. M. , D. P. H. , ( July 7 , 1857 -- January 6 , 1929 ) , Commissioner of Public Health , was a physician and surgeon of the early North West Territories in Canada .

David E. Carter is an entrepreneur and writer on graphic design , logo design , and corporate branding .
Jack Cassinetto is a plein air painter of the tonalism movement .
Stephen L. Carter ( born October 26 , 1954 ) is an American law professor at Yale University , legal- and social - policy writer , columnist , and best - selling novelist .
Judy Birmingham is a prominent English historical archaeologist , who has been based in Sydney , Australia for most of her career .
John Balguy ( August 12 , 1686 -- September 21 , 1748 ) was an English divine and philosopher .
Francesca Martinez ( born 1978 ) is an English stand - up comedian , writer and actress , born in London to a Spanish father and half - Swedish , half - English mother .

The Galápagos green turtle ( Chelonia agassizii ) used to be classified as a subspecies of the green sea turtle ( Chelonia mydas ) but was changed for a few reasons .
The Smerinthinae are a sub - family of Sphingidae moths in the order Lepidoptera .

Hippasteria phrygiana is a sea star species , member of the Goniasteridae family .
Peltandra primaeva is an extinct species of monocot in the Araceae family known from a Ypresian age Eocene fossil found in western North Dakota , USA .
Piesmatidae is a small family of true bugs , commonly called ash - grey leaf bugs .
Heterotheca rutteri , called the Huachuca goldenaster or Rutter 's false goldenaster , is a rare North American species of flowering plant in the aster family .
The petaltails of the family Petaluridae are apparently the most ancient of the extant true dragonflies ( infraorder Anisoptera ) , having fossil members from as early as the Jurassic ( over 150 million years ago ) .
Apera is a small genus of annual grasses , known commonly as silkybent grass or windgrass .
Sesamothamnus lugardii ( Transvaal sesame - bush , sesambos ) is a species of plant in family Pedaliaceae , endemic to southern Namibia , eastern Botswana , southern Zimbabwe , and Kruger National Park in the Transvaal .
Caulanthus pilosus is a species of flowering plant in the mustard family known by the common names hairy wild cabbage and chocolate drops .
Schismatorhynchos is a genus of cyprinid fish found in Asia .
Silaum silaus was one of the many species described by Carl Linnaeus in Volume I of the 1753 edition of his Species Plantarum as Peucedanum silaus .
Spinyfins are a family , Diretmidae , of beryciform fishes .
Phyllonemus is a genus of claroteid catfish native to Africa where it is only found in Lake Tanganyika .
Zonosaurus boettgeri is a species of lizard endemic to northern Madagascar , including Nosy Be .
Chicoreus banksii , common name the Banks ' murex , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Muricidae , the murex snails or rock snails .
Dynoides elegans is a species of isopod crustacean in the genus Dynoides .
Therizinosaurus ( /ˌθɛrɪˌzɪnoʊˈsɔːrəs/ ; ' scythe lizard ' , from the Greek therizo meaning ' to reap ' or ' to cut off ' and sauros meaning ' lizard ' ) is a genus of very large theropod dinosaurs .
Distocambarus is a genus of freshwater crayfish endemic to the United States .
Pararasbora moltrechti , Moltrecht 's minnow , is a species of cyprinid fish endemic to Taiwan .
Schoenoplectus hallii is a species of flowering plant in the sedge family known by the common name Hall 's bulrush .
Rhinella ( Beaked Toads or Rio Viejo Toads ) is a subgenus of Bufo ( treated by some as a distinct genus ) containing 71 species of true toads native to Neotropical Central and South America .
Parabrotula is a genus of false brotulas .
Tima formosa is a colonial species of marine hydrozoa in the family Conica .
Mystus albolineatus ( known locally as trey kanchos bay ) is a species of catfish endemic to Cambodia , Thailand and Vietnam , known from Chao Phraya River , Bang Pakong River , Mekong River and Tonlé Sap .
Eurocephalus is a small genus of passerine birds in the shrike family .
Pavlovia is an extinct genus of ammonite of the Late Jurassic to Late Cretaceous ( age range : 150.8 to 99.7 Ma ) .
Amanita pachycolea , commonly known as the western grisette , is a species of agaric fungus in the family Amanitaceae .
Like a number of other related cormorant species , the Cape cormorant is placed by some authorities ( e.g. Johnsgaard ) in the genus Leucocarbo .
Acaiu spinosus is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , and the only species in the genus Acaiu .
Hypodynerus is a South American , primarily Andean , genus of potter wasps with most of its described species inhabiting Chile .
Gandakasia is an extinct genus of ambulocetid from Pakistan , that lived in the Eocene epoch .
Hypuronector is a genus of extinct reptile from the Triassic Period that lived in what is now New Jersey .
Yoshinagella japonica is a fungus and the type species in the genus Yoshinagella .
Muricopsis matildae is a species of small sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Muricidae , the rock snails .
Gagata cenia is a species of sisorid catfish found in the Ganges Delta and the Indus River .
Lythrum alatum , commonly known as winged loosestrife , winged lythrum or ( in Britain and Ireland ) angled purple - loosestrife , is a species of flowering plant belonging to the family Lythraceae .
Cleistesiopsis divaricata is a terrestrial species of orchid native to the eastern United States from New Jersey to Florida .
Sipunculidea is a class of marine peanut worms .
Struthideidae is a family of passerine birds known as the Australian mudnesters .
Callistele calliston , common name the beautiiful top shell , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Trochidae ( unassigned to a subfamily ) .
Corriebaatar is the type and only genus of Corriebaataridae , a family of multituberculate mammals .
Hypoptopoma spectabile is a species of armoured catfish native to the Amazon and Orinoco river basins in Colombia , Ecuador , Peru and Venezuela .
Dichelostemma ida - maia is a species of flowering plant known as firecracker flower .
Magnolia grandiflora was one of the many species first described by Linnaeus in his Systema Naturae in 1759 , basing his description on the earlier notes of Miller .
Diplocynodon is an extinct genus of alligatoroid that lived during the Paleocene to middle Miocene 49 million years ago in Europe .
Braemia vittata is a species of orchid and the only species of genus Braemia .
Scalidiopsis youngi is a species of beetles in the family Passandridae , and the only species in the genus Scalidiopsis .
Phragmipedium vittatum is a species of orchid endemic to west - central and southeastern Brazil .
Puperita pupa is a species of small sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Neritidae , the nerites .
Eutricha capensis , the Cape lappet moth , is a species of moth in the family Lasiocampidae primarily found in South Africa .
Acanthopleuribacter is a genus in the phylum Acidobacteria ( bacteria ) .
Aquilegia caerulea is a species of Aquilegia flower native to the Rocky Mountains from Montana south to New Mexico and west to Idaho and Arizona .
Thomasia is a genus of plants which are native to southern Australia .
Phytophthora quercina is a papillate homothallic soil - borne plant pathogen causing root rot of oak tree species in Europe .
Euscorpius is a genus of scorpions , commonly called small wood - scorpions .
Formosibittacus is an extinct genus of hangingfly in the family Bittacidae and containing a single species Formosibittacus macularis .
Neithea is an extinct genus of bivalve mollusks that lived from the Early Jurassic to the early Paleocene , with a worldwide distribution .
Mycetophagus punctatus , sometimes called the hairy fungus beetle , is a species of fungus beetle .
Bannapone mulanae is a species of ant of the genus Bannapone , described in by Xu in 2000 .
Tetilla is a plant genus of the Melianthaceae family .
Lepidobatrachus llanensis ( common name : llanos frog ; in Spanish : escuerzo ) is a species of frog in the Ceratophryidae family .
Wolffia arrhiza is a species of flowering plant known by the common names spotless watermeal and rootless duckweed , belonging to the Araceae , a family rich in water - loving species , such as Arum and Pistia .
Sayella fusca , common name the brown sayella , is a species of minute sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk or micromollusk in the family Pyramidellidae , the pyrams and their allies .
Carpobrotus glaucescens , commonly known as angular sea - fig or pigface , is a species of flowering plant in the ice plant family .
Plectorhinchus picus , the painted sweetlips , is a species of grunt native to coral reefs of the Indian Ocean and the western Pacific Ocean at depths of 3 to 50 m ( 9.8 to 164.0 ft ) .
Neacomys paracou , also known as the Paracou neacomys or Paracou bristly mouse , is a rodent species from South America in the genus Neacomys .
Sterculia schliebenii is a species of plant in the Sterculiaceae family .
Neanis is an extinct genus of bird probably related to woodpeckers and toucans .
Lonicera interrupta is a species of honeysuckle known by the common name chaparral honeysuckle .
Loensia variegata is a species of Psocoptera from Liposcelididae family that can be found in Great Britain and Ireland .
Nereis is a genus of polychaete worms in the family Nereidae .
African elephants are elephants of the genus Loxodonta ( from the Greek words loxo ( oblique sided ) and donta ( tooth ) ) .
Tortrix sinapina , the Japanese oak leafroller , is a species of moth of the Tortricidae family .
Ceanothus verrucosus is a species of shrub in the buckthorn family Rhamnaceae known by the common names wart - stem ceanothus , barranca brush , and white coast ceanothus .
Struzl 's onion ( Allium struzlianum ) is a species of onion that is endemic to Armenia .
Pseudosiobla campbelli is an extinct species of sawfly in the family Tenthredinidae that is known from early Eocene Ypresian stage lake deposits near the unincorporated community of Horsefly , British Columbia .
Tsuga heterophylla , the western hemlock or western hemlock - spruce , is a species of hemlock native to the west coast of North America , with its northwestern limit on the Kenai Peninsula , Alaska , and its southeastern limit in northern Sonoma County , California .
Melica parodiana is a species of grass in the Poaceae family that can be found in Buenos Aires , Argentina and Uruguay .
Penicillium restingae is a species of the genus of Penicillium which was isolated from soil of the Guaibim sandbank in Bahia in Brazil .
Euschistospiza is a genus of birds in the family Estrildidae , found in Sub - Saharan Africa .
Altispinax ( /ˌæltɨˈspaɪnæks/ ; `` with high spines '' ) is a genus of large predatory theropod dinosaur from the Early Cretaceous ( Barremian ) Obernkirchen Sandstein of Niedersachsen , Germany .
Berberis actinacantha is a species of plant also known as michay .
Leptotyphlops brasiliensis , or the Brazilian blind snake , is a species of snake in the Leptotyphlopidae family .
Auchenipterus is a genus of driftwood catfishes ( order Siluriformes ) .
It contains only one species ( Polyvena horatius ) which was described from Dominican amber .
Coryphopterus is a genus of gobies mostly found in the western Atlantic Ocean though a couple species are found in the Indian and/or Pacific oceans .
Salix barrattiana is a species of flowering plant in the willow family known by the common name Barratt 's willow .
Adenomus is a small genus of true toads , with only three species , endemic to Sri Lanka .
Lobelia erinus ( edging lobelia , garden lobelia or trailing lobelia ) is a species of Lobelia native to southern Africa , from Malawi and Namibia south to South Africa .
Mentzelia mollis is a species of flowering plant in the Loasaceae known by the common names soft blazingstar , smooth blazingstar , and smooth stickleaf .
Arctides is a genus of slipper lobsters , containing three species .
Tetramolopium rockii is a rare species of flowering plant in the aster family known by the common name dune tetramolopium .
Schizaster is a genus of heart urchins belonging to the family Schizasteridae .
The species name was accepted as Crithidia deanei until 2011 , when phylogenetic analysis revealed that it belongs to the genus Angomonas , thereby becoming Angomonas deanei .
Paederia is a genus of flowering plants in the madder family , Rubiaceae .
Melica ciliata , commonly called hairy melic or silky spike melic , is a grass species of perennial bunchgrass native to Europe , north Africa , and temperate Asia .
Tropidia scita is a common European species of hoverfly associated with wetlands , ponds , ditches etc . The larvae have been recorded living in the basal sheaths of Typha .
Combretum molle , the velvet bushwillow , is a plant species in the genus Combretum found in West- , East- and South Africa .
Trachelipus rucneri is a species of woodlouse in the genus Trachelipus belonging to the family Trachelipodidae that can be found in Croatia .
Melica torreyana is a species of grass known by the common name Torrey 's melicgrass .
Botaurus is a genus of bitterns , a group of wading bird in the heron family Ardeidae .
The Orizaba long - tailed shrew ( Sorex orizabae ) is a species of mammal in the family Soricidae .
Astragalus alpinus is a species of flowering plant in the legume family known by the common name alpine milkvetch .
Nannacara is a genus of small freshwater cichlid fish endemic to South America .
Uropeltis macrolepis , commonly known as the Bombay earth snake , is a species of snake in the family Uropeltidae .
Paracorrhenes flavomaculata is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , and the only species in the genus Paracorrhenes .
Musa azizii is a species of wild banana ( genus Musa ) , native to Sarawak , Malaysia .
Salarias ramosus , the Starry blenny , is a species of combtooth blenny from the Western Central Pacific .
Prodasineura is a genus of damselflies in the family Protoneuridae .
Yaoshania pachychilus , the panda loach , is a species of gastromyzontid loach endemic to mountain streams in Jinxiu County , Guangxi in China .
Choeroichthys latispinosus , also known as the Muiron Island pipefish or Muiron pipefish , is a species of pipefish native to the western coast of Australia .
Exguiana postflavida is a species of snout moth in the genus Exguiana .
Carabus henningi is a species of ground beetle in the Carabinae subfamily that can be found in Mongolia and Russia .
Chiloglanis batesii is a species of upside - down catfish found widely in Western and Central Africa .
Agorius constrictus is a species of ant mimicking jumping spider from Singapore .
Sardinella melanura ( blacktip sardinella ) is a species of ray - finned fish in the genus Sardinella .
Crataegus boyntonii is a species of hawthorn native to the Southeastern U.S. Its fruit are `` yellow - green flushed with red '' .
Bangia is an extant genus of division Rhodophyta that grows in marine or freshwater habitats .
Abutilon × hybridum is a species name used for a wide variety of different types flowering plants of uncertain origin in the genus Abutilon .
Amycolatopsis rifamycinica is a species of Gram - positive bacteria in the Amycolatopsis genus .
The Attelabidae is a widespread family of weevils .
Magnetococcus marinus is a species of Alphaproteobacteria that has the peculiar ability to form a structure called a magnetosome , a membrane encased single - magnetic - domain mineral crystals formed by biomineralisation , which allows the cells to orientate along the Earth 's geomagnetic field .
Achirus is a genus of American soles native to tropical and subtropical parts of the Americas .
Amomyrtus luma , known as Luma , is a species of tree in the Myrtaceae family .
Clausidium dissimile is a species of copepod that has been found along the Atlantic and Gulf Coasts from Massachusetts to Florida .
Eriochloa sericea is a species of grass known by the common name Texas cupgrass .
Chylismiella pterosperma is a species of evening primrose known by the common name wingfruit suncup and is the only species in the monotypic genus Chylismiella .
Hydrobius fuscipes is a species of beetle in the family Hydrophilidae that is found across much of the temperate Northern Hemisphere .
Microhyla achatina ( commonly known as the Javan chorus frog ) is a species of narrow - mouthed frog found in Java .
Croton californicus is a species of croton known by the common name California croton .
Centaurea montana ( perennial cornflower , mountain cornflower , bachelor 's button , montane knapweed or mountain bluet ) is a species of Centaurea endemic to Europe .
Solanum sandwicense is a rare species of flowering plant in the nightshade family known by the common names Hawai'i horsenettle and popolo ' aiakeakua .
Oligodon ancorus , commonly known as the northern short - headed snake , is a species of colubrid snake found on the islands of Luzon and Mindoro in the Philippines , and the island of Sumatra in Indonesia .
Pisonia graciliscens is a species of plant in the Nyctaginaceae family .
Shorea smithiana ( also called Light Red Meranti ) is a large emergent rainforest tree species in the Dipterocarpaceae family .
Canthigaster figueiredoi , known as the Southern Atlantic sharpnose - puffer , is a species of marine fish in the family Tetraodontidae .
Macbridea alba is a rare species of flowering plant in the mint family known by the common name white birds - in - a - nest .
Artopoetes is a genus of butterfly in the family Lycaenidae . It is a small east Asian genus of tailless hairstreaks .
Lingulata is a class of brachiopod , among the oldest of all brachiopods having existed since the Cambrian period ( 541 million years ago ) .
Craibia brevicaudata is a species of medium to large evergreen trees from Fabaceae family that can be found in Angola , Ethiopia , Kenya , Malawi , Mozambique , Tanzania , Zaire , Zambia , and Zimbabwe .
Bunias orientalis , the Turkish wartycabbage , warty - cabbage , hill mustard , or Turkish rocket , is a plant species in the genus Bunias .
Populus adenopoda , known commonly as the Chinese aspen , is a species of poplar found in China .
Dorylus gribodoi is a West African species of army ants in the genus Dorylus .
Stanhopea florida is a species of orchid occurring from Ecuador to Peru .
Chaetodon pelewensis also known as the dot dash butterflyfish , Spotbanded Butterflyfish , Punctato Butterflyfish , or Spot - band Butterflyfish is a fish species native to Indonesia and has a yellow - tan body .
Munidopsis polymorpha is a species of squat lobster ( also known as the blind albino cave crab ) that is endemic to Lanzarote , Canary Islands .
Rumex patientia , known as patience dock , `` garden patience '' , `` herb patience '' , or `` monk 's rhubarb '' , is a herbaceous perennial plant species of the genus Rumex , belonging to the family Polygonaceae .
Microhexura is a tiny spider genus from the USA with only two species .
The bicolor butterflyfish , Prognathodes dichrous , is a species of butterflyfish found in atlantic waters .
Pomadasys commersonnii , the smallspotted grunter , is a species of grunt native to the shores of the western Indian Ocean from India to South Africa , being found in brackish and marine waters and occasionally into fresh waters .
Gymnanthes lucida , commonly known as shiny oysterwood or crabwood , is a species of flowering plant in the spurge family , Euphorbiaceae , that is native to southern Florida in the United States , the Bahamas , the Caribbean , Mexico , and Central America .
Plioviverrops is an extinct genus of terrestrial carnivore of the family Hyaenidae , endemic to Southern Europe during the Late Miocene subepoch ( 11.6 - -5.3 mya ) existing for approximately 6.3 million years .
Cyamiidae is a family of marine bivalve clams of the order Veneroida .
Badis khwae is a species of freshwater fish native to Thailand .
Cotysomerida lampyroides is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , and the only species in the genus Cotysomerida .
Pheidochloa is a genus of Australian and Papuasian plants in the grass family .
Piatnitzkysaurus ( pron.:``PEA - at - NITS - key - SORE - us '' ) is an extinct genus of megalosauroid theropod dinosaur that lived approximately 164 to 161 million years ago during the middle part of the Jurassic Period in what is now Argentina .
Andrena hattorfiana is a species of mining bees belonging to the family Andrenidae subfamily Andreninae .
Conasprella sieboldii , common name Siebold 's cone , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Conidae , the cone snails and their allies .
Xiurenbagrus gigas is a species of catfish of the family Amblycipitidae .
Anolis lividus , the Plymouth anole , is a species of anole lizard that is endemic to the island of Montserrat in the Caribbean Lesser Antilles .
Sideroxylon celastrinum is a species of flowering plant in the sapodilla family , Sapotaceae , that is native to Texas and Florida in the United States south through Central America to northern Venezuela and Colombia in South America .
Andricus kollari is species of wasp which causes the formation of marble galls on oak trees .
Melica harfordii is a species of grass known by the common name Harford 's oniongrass .
Acanthosaura is a genus of lizards commonly known as mountain horned dragons , or pricklenape agamas .
Penicillium rubidurum is an anamorph , monoverticillate species of the genus of Penicillium .
A monotypic genus , it contains the single species Kruphaiomyces trochoidei .
Lohoodon is a genus of hapalodectid mesonychians which lived during the middle Eocene .
Denticetopsis iwokrama is a species of whale catfish endemic to Guyana where it is only known from the type locality in the Siparuni River basin .
Dardanus venosus , the starry - eyed crab or stareye crab , is a species of hermit crab in the family Diogenidae .
Salpichroa origanifolia is a species of flowering plant in the nightshade family known by the common names lily of the valley vine , pampas lily - of - the - valley or cock's - eggs .
Ophelina acuminata is a species of marine annelids , found in the sublittoral mud and sand bottom .
The soldier flies ( Stratiomyidae , sometimes misspelled as Stratiomyiidae , from Greek στρατιώτης - soldier ; μυια - fly ) are a family of flies ( historically placed in the now - obsolete group Orthorrhapha ) .
Plagiobothrys hirtus , the rough popcornflower , is a plant species with only about a dozen reportedly extant occurrences , all within the Umpqua River watershed in Douglas County , Oregon .
This is a monotypic genus , containing the single species Pseudoperitheca murmanica .
Lithocarpus kingii is a species of plant in the family Fagaceae .
Haliotis rubiginosa , common name the Lord Howe abalone , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Haliotidae , the abalones .
Salix floridana , the Florida willow , is a species of willow in the family Salicaceae .
The superfamily Trichoceroidea includes one family :
Cassytha filiformis , common name love - vine , is a species of obligate parasitic vine in the family Lauraceae .
Deinandra bacigalupii ( sometimes misspelled bacigalupi ) is a rare species of flowering plant in the aster family known by the common names Livermore tarplant and Livermore moonshine .
Sphenocephalus is an extinct genus of ray - finned fish that lived during the Cretaceous period .
Blepharizonia plumosa is a California species of tarweed known by the common name big tarweed .
The Opluridae , or Madagascan iguanas , are a family of moderately sized lizards native to Madagascar and Grande Comore .
Nacella kerguelenensis is a southern , cold - water species of limpet , a marine gastropod mollusc in the family Nacellidae , the true limpets .
Heterospathe is a monoecious genus of flowering plant in the palm family found in Oceania , where it is called sagisi palm .
Samoana attenuata is a species of air - breathing tropical land snail , a terrestrial pulmonate gastropod mollusk in the family Partulidae .
Puntius dolichopterus is a species of fish in the family Cyprinidae .
Lithospermum canescens is a species of flowering plant known by the common name hoary puccoon .
Ecsenius namiyei , commonly called Black comb - tooth or Namiye 's coralblenny , is a species of marine fish in the family Blenniidae .
The Phronimidae are a family of amphipod crustaceans , containing two genera :
Erigeron mariposanus is a rare species of flowering plant in the daisy family known by the common names foothill fleabane , Mariposa daisy , or Mariposa erigeron .
Eupatorium anomalum , commonly called Florida thoroughwort , is a North American species in the sunflower family .
Diplorhynchus is a monotypic genus of plant in the Apocynaceae family found in tropical and southern Africa .
Galium kamtschaticum , known as Kamchatka bedstraw or boreal bedstraw , is a plant species in the Rubiaceae , named for the Kamchatka Peninsula on the Pacific Coast of Russia .
Phanera variegata is a species of flowering plant in the family Fabaceae , native to South Asia and Southeast Asia , from southern China , Burma , India , Nepal , Pakistan , and Sri Lanka .
Oryzeae is a tribe of flowering plants in the true grass family , Poaceae .
Nannosquillidae is a family of stomatopods , comprising the following genera :
Rubus parliniiis a rare North American species of flowering plant in the rose family .
Pantophthalmidae is a small family of very large , robust flies , sometimes referred to as timber flies .
The Kentucky warbler ( Geothlypis formosa ) is a small species of New World warbler .
Rubus blanchardianus , Blanchard 's dewberry , is a rare North American species of flowering plant in the rose family .
Charonia tritonis , common name the Triton 's trumpet or the giant triton , is a species of very large sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusc in the family Ranellidae , the tritons .
Cyphoryctis xylodoma is a moth in the Xyloryctidae family , and the only species in the genus Cyphoryctis .
Dipteronia is a genus of two living and one extinct species , regarded in the soapberry family Sapindaceae sensu lato after Angiosperm Phylogeny Group ( APG I 1998 , APG II 2003 ) and more recently ( Harrington et al . 2005 ) ) or traditionally by several authors in Aceraceae , related to the maples .
Mermis nigrescens is a species of nematode known commonly as the grasshopper nematode .
It contains the single species Anthropodyptes gilli , known from a Middle Miocene humerus from Australia .
Phacelia austromontana is a species of phacelia known by the common name Southern Sierra phacelia .
Only one species is known , Entomophobia kinabaluensis , endemic to the Island of Borneo .
Chaptalia tomentosa , common name pineland daisy , is a plant species native to the southeastern United States .
Baenidae is an extinct family of cryptodiran turtles that first appeared during the Jurassic , and died out during the Eocene
Linatella caudata , common name : the Girdled triton or Poulsen 's Triton , is a species of predatory sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Ranellidae , the triton snails , triton shells or tritons .
Kempfidris is a Neotropical genus of ants in the subfamily Myrmicinae containing the single species Kempfidris inusualis .
Carolina chickadees are so similar to black - capped chickadees that they themselves have trouble telling their species apart .
Elaphrus lindrothi is a species of ground beetle in the subfamily Elaphrinae .
Goupia is a neotropical genus of flowering plants and the sole genus included in the family Goupiaceae .
Acer pilosum is an Asian species of maple .
It is the only species in the genus Prionium , and is endemic to South Africa ( Cape Province and KwaZulu - Natal ) .
Maylandia barlowi is a species of cichlid endemic to Lake Malawi where it is only known from the area around the Maleri Islands where it prefers areas with soft substrates .
Wolterstorffina ( the Wolterstorff toads ) is a genus of true toads native to Nigeria and Cameroon .
Excoecaria indica , is a mangrove species belonging to the genus Excoecaria of the family Euphorbiaceae .
Paraneoptera is a monophyletic superorder of insects which includes four orders , the bark lice , true lice , thrips , and hemipterans , the true bugs .
Grevillea alpivaga , also known as Buffalo Grevillea , is a species of the plant genus Grevillea .
Dimeria is a genus of Asian , Australian , Madagascan , and Pacific Island plants in the grass family .
Horkelia tridentata is a species of flowering plant in the rose family known by the common name threetooth horkelia .
Smilax hugeri , Huger 's carrionflower , is a North American plant species native to the southeastern United States .
Xinjiangtitan is an extinct genus of mamenchisaurid sauropod known from the Middle Jurassic Qigu Formation in Piqan County of Xinjiang , northwestern China .
Hazeus is a genus of gobies native to the Red Sea , the Indian Ocean and the northwestern Pacific Ocean .
Notochthamalus scabrosus , the only species in the genus Notochthamalus , is a species of barnacle found along the south - western and south - eastern coasts of South America , from Peru to the Falkland Islands .
Zeuzerocossus cinereus is a moth in the Cossidae family , and the only species in the genus Zeuzerocossus .
Hylarana milleti ( Millet 's frog or Dalat frog ) is a species of true frog in the genus Hylarana .
Beris geniculata , the long - horned black legionnaire , is a European species of soldier fly .
Nicotiana acuminata is a species of wild tobacco known by the English common name manyflower tobacco .
Tropisternus is a genus of hydrophilid beetles with 63 species in five subgenera in North and South America .
Palinurus barbarae is a species of spiny lobster described in 2006 , which was found by fishermen working the waters above the Walters Shoals , a series of submerged mountains 700 kilometres ( 430 mi ) south of Madagascar .
The type and only species , is Thalassiodracon hawkinsi Owen 1840 .
Oncidium pectorale is a species of orchid endemic to Brazil ( Rio de Janeiro ) .
Banksia sessilis var . cordata is a variety of Banksia sessilis ( Parrot Bush ) , with unusually large leaves and flower heads .
Lomatium congdonii , known by the common names Mariposa desertparsley and Congdon 's lomatium , is a species of flowering plant in the carrot family .
Buddleja sterniana was a species sunk as Buddleja crispa by Leeuwenberg in 1979 , and treated as such in the subsequent Flora of China .
The Seychelles scops owl ( Otus insularis ) , also known as bare - legged scops owl or syer ( in Creole ) is a rare scops owl species , which only occurs in the Morne Seychellois National Park on the Seychelles island of Mahé .
Warrenisuchus is an extinct genus of temnospondyl amphibian from the Early Triassic of Queensland , Australia .
Philoria is a genus of frogs native to eastern and southern Australia .
Nuculida is an order of small saltwater clams , marine bivalve mollusks .
Leuciscus baicalensis , or the Siberian dace , is a freshwater species of cyprinid fish , found in Siberian rivers draining to the Arctic Ocean , from the Ob to the Kolyma in the east , as well as in Mongolia and in Ulungur Lake and Ulungur River in Xinjiang , China .
Cupitha purreea , commonly known as the Wax Dart , is a butterfly belonging to the family Hesperiidae and only species of the Cupitha genus .
Aplysia vaccaria , also known as the black sea hare and California black sea hare , is a species of extremely large sea slug , a marine , opisthobranch , gastropod mollusk in the family Aplysiidae .
Lepidozia is a genus of liverwort in family Lepidoziaceae .
Lioprosopa haploa is a species of snout moth in the genus Lioprosopa .
Platyscapa is a genus of 19 species of pollinating fig wasps found in Africa and Madagascar , Middle East , southern Asia and the Indo - Pacific islands .
Cryptosporidium muris is a species of coccidium , first isolated from the gastric glands of the common mouse .
The Ceratocystidaceae are a family of fungi in the Sordariomycetes class , subclass Hypocreomycetidae .
Araiostegia is a genus of twelve epiphytic or terrestrial ferns from tropical Asia belonging to the hares - foot fern family .
Lithodytes lineatus ( Spanish : sapito listado ) is a species of frog in the Leptodactylidae family .
Tapeworms of the order Cyclophyllidea ( the cyclophyllid cestodes ) are the most important cestode parasites of humans and domesticated animals .
Amaryllis paradisicola is a species of bulbous perennial plant from South Africa .
Naraboryctes is an extinct genus of marsupial from early Miocene deposits of Boodjamulla National Park of Riversleigh area , northwestern Queensland , Australia .
Symphodus is a genus of wrasses native to the eastern Atlantic Ocean and the Mediterranean Sea .
Libinia ferreirae is a species of tropical spider crab in the family Epialtidae .
There is one named species , Afrovenator abakensis .
Neritina glabrata is a species of brackish water snail , a gastropod mollusk in the family Neritidae .
Eucharis candida is a plant species native to Colombia , Ecuador and Peru but cultivated as an ornamental in many other regions .
Clytostoma elegans is a flowering plant species in the genus Clytostoma .
Exarrhenodes flavosticticus is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , and the only species in the genus Exarrhenodes .
Pseudelasma curticornis is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , and the only species in the genus Pseudelasma .
Labrisomus wigginsi , the Baja blenny , is a species of labrisomid blenny endemic to the Pacific coast of Baja California .
Theosodon is an extinct genus of litoptern mammal from the early Miocene of South America .
Bellastraea rutidoloma , common name the granular small star , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Turbinidae , the turban snails .
Dysmachus trigonus , the fan - bristled robberfly , is a species of robber fly ( family Asilidae ) .
Thyrophorella thomensis is a species of small air - breathing land snail , a terrestrial pulmonate gastropod mollusk in the family Thyrophorellidae .
Tibia curta , common name the Indian tibia , is a species of large sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Strombidae , the true conchs .
Ephedra cutleri , the Navajo ephedra or Cutler 's jointfir , is a species of Ephedra that is native to the Southwestern United States ( Arizona , New Mexico , Utah , Colorado , Nevada , Wyoming ) .
Begonia incarnata is a species of plant in the family Begoniaceae , native to Brazil .
Melaleuca pustulata is sometimes confused with Melaleuca ericifolia which also occurs naturally in Tasmania , however the leaves of that species lack the raised oil glands of M. pustulata and the outer surface of its flower cup ( hypanthium ) is hairy .
Amphiesma parallelum , commonly known as the Yunnan keelback , is a species of natricine snake which is endemic to Asia .
Deinandra pentactis , called Salinas River tarweed , is a North American species of plants in the tarweed tribe within the ( sunflower family ) .
Miuroglanis platycephalus is a species of catfish ( order Siluriformes ) of the family Trichomycteridae , and the only species of the genus Miuroglanis .
Stenostiridae , or the fairy flycatchers , are a family of small passerine birds proposed as a result of recent discoveries in molecular systematics .
Prosthechea is a genus in the orchid family ( Orchidaceae ) .
Ceramium is a genus of red algae in the Rhodophyta .
Hydrophis brookii is a species of venomous sea snake .
The Anthocoridae are a family of bugs , commonly called minute pirate bugs or flower bugs .
Eriogonum plumatella is a species of wild buckwheat known by the common name yucca buckwheat .
Juncus trifidus is a species of rush known by the common names highland rush and three - leaved rush .
Triacanthidae , commonly known as triplespines or tripodfishes , is a family of Indo - Pacific fishes .
Pristimantis lemur ( in Spanish : rana picuda ) is a species of frog in the Craugastoridae family .
Stenoponia americana is a species of large flea in the family Hystrichopsyllidae .
Benthophilus grimmi is a species of goby widespread in the northern Caspian Sea at depth 80 to 240 metres ( 260 to 790 ft ) .
Oxyrhopus melanogenys , commonly known as Tschudi 's false coral snake , is a colubrid snake species found in the northern part of South America .
Omobranchus fasciolatoceps is a species of combtooth blenny found in the northwest Pacific ocean , around southern Japan and China .
Bolma pseudobathyraphis is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Turbinidae , the turban snails .
The genus Sarcochilus , abbreviated as Sarco .
Dipterocarpus zeylanicus , commonly known as හොර - Hora in Sinhalese and සරල - Sarala or කිරිපලු - Kiripalu in Sanskrit , is a species of Dipterocarpus that is endemic to Sri Lanka .
It contains only one known species , Didymocistus chrysadenius , native to the Loreto region of northeastern Peru , the Amazonas Department of southeastern Colombia , and the State of Amazonas in northwestern Brazil .
The Campo oriole or Campo troupial ( Icterus jamacaii ) is a species of bird in the family Icteridae .
Compsomantis tumidiceps is a species of praying mantis found in Java , Lombok , the Philippine Islands , Sumatra , Sumba , and Timor .
Alsodes monticola ( common name : island spiny - chest frog ) is a species of frog in the Alsodidae family .
Archontophoenicinae is a botanical subtribe consisting of four genera of palms , namely Archontophoenix from Queensland and New South Wales and Actinokentia , Chambeyronia and Kentiopsis from New Caledonia .
Gilia aliquanta is a species of flowering plant in the phlox family known by the common name puffcalyx gilia .
Sphenophorus abbreviatus is a true weevil species in the genus Sphenophorus .
Myosotis latifolia is a species of forget - me - not known by the common name broadleaf forget - me - not .
Heteroclinus eckloniae , the Kelp weedfish , is a species of clinid native to the Indo - Pacific waters of the southern coast of Australia where it can be found in kelp and algal reefs .
Streptomyces hainanensis is a bacterium species from the genus of Streptomyces which has been isolated from soil in from the island Hainan in China .
Neolitsea sericea is a species of a medium - sized evergreen tree up to 10 m ( 33 ft ) tall in the Lauraceae family .
Amblyodipsas dimidiata , or the Mpwapwa purple - glossed snake , is a species of venomous rear - fanged snake in the Atractaspididae family .
Cambaroides wladiwostokensis is a species of crayfish endemic to Primorsky Krai .
Pentanema is a genus of Asian and African plants in the elecampane tribe within the sunflower family .
Angraecum podochiloides is a species of comet orchid that can be found in Cameroon , the Democratic Republic of the Congo , Côte d'Ivoire , Equatorial Guinea , Gabon , Ghana , Liberia and Nigeria .
The Craugastoridae , or fleshbelly frogs , are a family of New World direct - developing frogs .
Aconopteroides laevipennis is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , and the only species in the genus Aconopteroides .
Cryptosporidium is a genus of apicomplexan protozoans that can cause a respiratory and gastrointestinal illness ( cryptosporidiosis ) that primarily involves watery diarrhea ( intestinal cryptosporidiosis ) with or without a persistent cough ( respiratory cryptosporidiosis ) in both immunocompetent and immunodeficient humans .
Argoctenus is a genus of spider from the Miturgidae family .
Pareuxesta academica is a species of ulidiid or picture - winged fly in the genus Pareuxesta of the family Ulidiidae .
Ulva acanthophora is a species of benthic subtropical seaweed in Ulvaceae family that can be found in Baja , California and Mexico .
Thenaria is an infraorder of cnidarian anthozoans of the suborder Nyantheae , order Actiniaria .
Micromastra isoldalis is a species of snout moth , and the only species in the genus Micromastra .
Eutrombicula splendens is a species of chigger .
Austroponera is a ponerine genus of ants found in Australia and New Zealand .
Picea breweriana , known as Brewer spruce , Brewer 's weeping spruce , or weeping spruce , is a species of spruce native to western North America , where it is one of the rarest on the continent , endemic to the Klamath Mountains of southwest Oregon and northwest California .
Pseuderanthemum reticulatum , common names Yellow - Vein Eranthemum and Golden Pseuderanthemum , is a species of evergreen shrub in the Acanthaceae family .
Ceanothus parvifolius is a species of shrub in the buckthorn family Rhamnaceae known by the common name littleleaf ceanothus .
Masdevallia tovarensis is a species of orchid endemic to northern Venezuela .
Logania is a genus of plants belonging to the family Loganiaceae .
Randia portoricensis , known commonly as the Puerto Rico Indigoberry , is a species of shrub in the family Rubiaceae .
Monodilepas monilifera cookiana is a subspecies of small sea snail , a keyhole limpet , a subspecies of marine gastropod mollusc in the family Fissurellidae , the keyhole limpets and slit limpets .
Diptychus is a genus of cyprinid fish , consisting of two Asian species .
Thelypodium crispum is a species of flowering plant in the mustard family known by the common name crisped thelypody .
Streptaxidae is a taxonomic family of carnivorous air - breathing land snails , terrestrial pulmonate gastropod mollusks in the clade Stylommatophora .
Lioptilodes parafuscicostatus is a species of moth in the genus Lioptilodes , known from Ecuador and possibly Peru .
Turbo reevei , common name the Reeve 's turban , is a species of sea snail , marine gastropod mollusk in the family Turbinidae .
Senecio hydrophiloides is a species of flowering plant in the aster family known by the common names tall groundsel and sweet marsh ragwort .
Emblemaria vitta , the Ribbon blenny , is a species of chaenopsid blenny found around Navassa Island , in the western central Atlantic ocean .
Turbo cailletii , common name the filose turban , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Turbinidae , the turban snails .
Omus dejeani is a species of flightless tiger beetle ( Cicindelidae ) that is found from British Columbia almost to northern California in dense , coastal forests .
Neotinea tridentata ( three - toothed orchid ) is a species of orchid found in southern Europe from Spain to Turkey and Lebanon ; northwards to the Crimea , Poland and Germany .
Ephedra breana ( frutilla de campo , pingo - pingo ) is a species of Ephedra growing from northwest Argentina through to Chile and Bolivia .
Antimargarita is a genus of sea snails , marine gastropod mollusks in the family Margaritidae .
Alidopsis latefasciatus is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , and the only species in the genus Alidopsis .
Allium rotundum , common name round - headed leek or purple - flowered garlic , is a Eurasian and North African species of wild onion .
Myrmica bibikoffi is a species of ant that can be found in Germany , and Switzerland .
Eolepidopterix is an extinct genus of moths within the family Eolepidopterigidae , containing one species , Eolepidopterix jurassica , which is known from Russia .
Yochelcionella is an extinct genus of basal molluscs which lived during the Tommotian epoch , the first epoch of the Cambrian period .
It is the only species in the genus Guatemalteca .
Xixiasaurus is a genus of extinct troodontid dinosaur from the Late Cretaceous of modern - day China .
Cymatium lotorium , common name Black - spotted or Washing Bath Triton , is a species of predatory sea snail , a tropical marine gastropod mollusc in the family Ranellidae , the tritons .
Trypauchenichthys is a genus of gobies native to fresh , brackish and marine waters along the Indian Ocean and Pacific coasts of Asia .
Tetrazygia bicolor ( Pronunciation : tet - truh - ZIG - ee - uh BI - cull - ler ) is a species flowering plant in the glory bush family , Melastomataceae , that is native to southern Florida in the United States and the Caribbean .
Inermocoelotes paramicrolepidus is a funnel - web spider species found in Greece .
Paragonimus westermani is the major species of lung fluke to infects humans , causing paragonimiasis .
The Majagua ( Hampea reynae ) is a species of flowering plant in the Malvaceae family .
Handleyomys is a genus of Central and South American rodents in the tribe Oryzomyini of family Cricetidae .
Panulirus longipes , the longlegged spiny lobster , is a species of spiny lobster that lives on shallow rocky and coral reefs in the tropical Indo - Pacific region .
Anthemis carpatica ( Snow Carpet ) is a species of the genus Anthemis and in the Asteraceae family .
Cyathea brownii , commonly known as the Norfolk tree fern or smooth tree fern , is probably the largest tree fern species in the world .
Megacephala regalis is a species of ground beetle in the subfamily of Carabinae that was described by Boherman in 1848 .
Nebria coiffaiti is a species of ground beetle from Nebriinae subfamily that is endemic to Turkey .
Sapphirina , also called the sea sapphires , is a genus of parasitic copepod , containing the following species :
Hexagenia bilineata is a species of mayfly in the family Ephemeridae .
Rhizanthes is a genus of 4 species of parasitic flowering plants without leaves , stems , roots , or photosynthetic tissue .
Carex petasata is a species of sedge known by the common name Liddon sedge .
Cleome maculata is a species of cleome that is native to southern Africa , where it occurs in sandy soils , especially in rocky habitats , and on slopes .
Phyllococcus oahuensis was a species of mealybug in the family Pseudococcidae , and the only species in the genus Phyllococcus .
The Colombian small - eared shrew ( Cryptotis colombiana ) is a species of mammal in the family Soricidae .
Anthocharis cardamines phoenissa is a subspecies of Orange Tip butterfly found mostly in the Middle East .
Geastrum rufescens , commonly known as the rosy earthstar , is a species of fungus in the family Geastraceae .
Ristella guentheri , commonly known as Günther 's Ristella , is a species of skink endemic to India .
Eleocharis parishii is a species of spikesedge known by the common name Parish 's spikerush .
Pristichampsidae is an extinct family of crocodilians that lived in Europe , Asia , and North America during the Paleogene .
Astragalus bolanderi is a species of milkvetch known by the common name Bolander 's milkvetch .
Taphrognathus is an extinct genus of conodont named in 1941 .
Lysimachia clethroides , common name gooseneck loosestrife , is a species of flowering plant , traditionally classified in the family Primulaceae .
Thelypodium eucosmum is a species of flowering plant in the mustard family known by the common names arrow - leaf thelypody and world thelypody .
Bacillus horti is a species of Gram - negative alkaliphilic bacillus .
Farlowella altocorpus is a species of armored catfish endemic to Bolivia where it occurs in the Coroico River .
The Alteromonadales are an order of Proteobacteria .
Capsicum chinense , commonly known as `` yellow lantern chili '' , is a species of chili pepper native to the Americas .
Aequatorium repandiforme is a species of flowering plant in the Asteraceae family that is found only in Ecuador .
Tripsacum laxum , the Guatemalan gamagrass , is a species of grass in the Poaceae family .
Desulfovibrio vulgaris is a species of Gram - negative sulfate - reducing bacteria in the Desulfovibrionaceae family .
Penstemon clutei is a species of flowering plant in the plantain family known by the common name Sunset Crater beardtongue .
Bursatella leachii , common name the ragged sea hare or shaggy sea hare , is a species of large sea slug or sea hare , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Aplysiidae , the sea hares .
Apistogramma eremnopyge is a species of cichlid .
Paramonacanthus is a genus of filefishes native to the Indian and Pacific Oceans .
The Lavasoa dwarf lemur ( Cheirogaleus lavasoensis ) is a small , nocturnal strepsirrhine primate and a species of lemur that is endemic to three small , isolated patches of forest on the southern slopes of the Lavasoa Mountains in southern Madagascar .
Conus excelsus , common name the excelsior cone or the illustrious cone , is a species of predatory sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Conidae , the cone snails .
Manidens is a genus of heterodontosaurid dinosaur from the Middle Jurassic of Patagonia .
Hyloxalus whymperi , sometimes known as the Tanti rocket frog , is a species of frog in the Dendrobatidae family .
Leptotyphlops bicolor , or the two - colored blind snake , is a species of snake in the Leptotyphlopidae family .
Abralia is a genus of squid comprising around 20 species .
Psidium friedrichsthalianum , the Costa Rican guava or cas , is a species of guava found mostly in Costa Rica but also grown in Guatemala , Nicaragua and other Central American countries .
Squilla mantis is a species of mantis shrimp found in shallow coastal areas of the Mediterranean Sea and the Eastern Atlantic Ocean .
Munnozia is a genus of flowering plants in the aster family , Asteraceae .
Conraua crassipes is a species of frog in the Conrauidae family found in Cameroon , the Republic of the Congo , the Democratic Republic of the Congo , Equatorial Guinea , Gabon , Nigeria , and possibly Angola and the Central African Republic .
The genus contains only one species , Cladarctia quadriramosa , which is found in Tibet , Nepal , Kashmir and the northwestern Himalayas .
Rhus lanceolata , the prairie sumac , is a plant species native to Texas , Oklahoma , Arizona , New Mexico , Coahuila , Nuevo León and Tamaulipas .
Trichogaster is a genus of gouramis native to South Asia from Pakistan to Myanmar .
Pellona ditchela , called the Indian pellona , ditchelee and the toothed shad , is a species of longfin herring native to the coasts , mangrove swamps , and estuaries of the Indian Ocean and the western Pacific , generally in tropical waters .
Platydoras cataphractus also known as the Spiny catfish is a species of thorny catfish found in rivers of Bolivia , Brazil , Colombia , French Guiana , Guyana , Peru , and Suriname .
The Zeidae ( named after Zeus , the supreme god of Greek mythology ) are a family of large , showy , deep - bodied zeiform marine fish -- the `` true dories '' .
Magnapaulia is a genus of herbivorous lambeosaurine dinosaur known from the Latest Cretaceous Baja California , of northwestern Mexico .
Nebria cordicollis praegensis is a subspecies of black coloured ground beetle in the Nebriinae subfamily that is endemic to Seehalde , Germany .
Oioceros is an extinct genus of spiral - horned antelope from the late Miocene .
Epilasia is a genus of flowering plants in the daisy family .
Nannophryne variegata , known also as the Eden Harbour toad or Patagonian toad , is a species of toad in the family Bufonidae .
Etheostoma osburni , the candy darter or finescale saddled darter , is a species of darter endemic to the eastern United States where they are only known from the Kanawha River system in the states of Virginia and West Virginia .
Arctoperlaria is a suborder of stoneflies .
Acleistorhinus is an extinct genus of parareptile known from the Early Permian ( middle Kungurian stage ) of Oklahoma .
Acteniopsis is a genus of snout moths in the subfamily Pyralinae .
Hydra oligactis , also known as the brown hydra , is a species of hydra found widely dispersed in the northern temperate zone .
Pleurothallis cordata is a species of orchid occurring from western South America to Venezuela .
The Anisakidae are a family of intestinal roundworms .
Piliranova pilipes is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , and the only species in the genus Piliranova .
Indigofera tinctoria , also called true indigo , is a species of plant from the bean family that was one of the original sources of indigo dye .
Calotomus carolinus , commonly known as Carolines parrotfish , is a species of parrotfish .
Rhinoviruses is a genus within the Picornaviridae family of viruses .
Euphlyctis ghoshi ( Manipur frog , Ghosh 's frog ) is a species of frog found in Manipur , India .
Acanthiza is a genus of passeriform birds , mostly found in Australia but with one species ( A. murina ) restricted to New Guinea .
Donatia novae - zelandiae is a species of cushion plant in the family Donatiaceae and is closely related to species in the family Stylidiaceae .
Phymosoma is an extinct genus of echinoid that lived from the Cretaceous to the Eocene .
Sebastolobus is a genus of rockfishes native to the northern and eastern Pacific Ocean .

Polystachya concreta , the greater yellowspike orchid , is a species of orchid native to tropical and subtropical America , Africa and Asia .
Heliobolus lugubris , also known as the bushveld lizard , is a species of lizard in the genus Heliobolus native to southern Africa .
Prionurus is a genus of surgeonfishes found mostly in the Pacific Ocean with one species , P. biafraensis , native to the Atlantic Ocean .
Tilia tomentosa , known as silver linden in the US and silver lime in the UK , is a species of flowering plant in the family Malvaceae , native to southeastern Europe and southwestern Asia , from Hungary and the Balkans east to western Turkey , occurring at moderate altitudes .
Salvethymus svetovidovi , also called the long - finned charr , is a species of salmonid fish .
The genus is monotypic , containing the single species Geosiphon pyriformis , first described by Kützing in 1849 as Botrydium pyriforme .

Members of the family Narkidae are commonly known as sleeper rays .
Brickellia brachyphylla ( plumed brickellbush or Hinckley 's brickellbush ) is a North American species of flowering plant in the daisy family .

Sinopanorpa is a genus of scorpionflies .
Araxoceratidae is an extinct family of ceratitid ammonite cephalopods that were found throughout the world .

Polygonum cascadense is a species of flowering plant in the buckwheat family known by the common name Cascade knotweed .
