Mesorhizobium loti , formerly known as Rhizobium loti , is a Gram negative species of bacteria found in the root nodules of many plant species .
Santacruzodon is an extinct genus of synapsid which existed in Brazil during the Triassic period .
Aulacaspis yasumatsui , or cycad aulacaspis scale ( CAS ) , is a scale insect species in the genus Aulacaspis that feeds on cycad species such as Cycas revoluta or Dioon purpusii ( Purpus ' cycad ) .
Colchicum trigynum is a species of plants native to Turkey , Iran and the Caucasus , often grown as an ornamental plant outside its native range .
Acer pensylvanicum ( striped maple , also known as moosewood and moose maple ) is a small North American species of maple .
Ceratotherium mauritanicum is a species of fossil African rhinoceros found in the Late Pliocene to earliest Holocene of Morocco , Tunisia , and Algeria .
Crataegus pycnoloba is a species of hawthorn native to the mountains of the northern and central Peloponnesus of Greece .
Apocynum venetum is a plant species in the dogbane family , poisonous but used as a source of fiber , medicine , and nectar for production of honey .
Temnopleuridea is an infraorder of sea urchins in the order Camaradonta .
Ophrys omegaifera , the Omega Bee - orchid , is a species of orchid native to the Mediterranean region from Portugal and Morocco to Syria .
Paraplatyptilia sabourini and Paraplatyptilia watkinsi are cryptic species differentiated by diagnostic characters in female genitalia .
Hemiphylacus is a genus of flowering plants endemic to Mexico .
Anostoma octodentatum , common name Brazilian up - mouth snail , is a species of air - breathing land snail , a terrestrial pulmonate gastropod mollusk in the family Odontostomidae .
Pterobrycon is a genus of characins found in Colombia and Costa Rica .
The Two - flowered Bulbophyllum ( Bulbophyllum biflorum ) is a species of orchid .
Allium bolanderi is a species of wild onion known by the common name Bolander 's onion .
Labordia pumila ( Kauai labordia ) is a rare species of flowering plant in the Loganiaceae family .
Lecanicillium lecanii is now an approved name of an entomopathogenic fungus species , that was previously widely known as Verticillium lecanii ( Zimmerman ) Viegas ) , but is now understood to be an anamorphic form in the Cordyceps group of genera in the Clavicipitaceae .
Pangasius pangasius , the Pangas catfish , is a species of shark catfish native to fresh and brackish waters of Bangladesh , India , Myanmar , and Pakistan .
Coprinellus micaceus is a common species of fungus in the family Psathyrellaceae with a cosmopolitan distribution .
Cibotium regale , common name royal cibotium or royal Mexican tree fern , is a species of tropical tree fern belonging to the family Cibotiaceae .
Eleutherodactylus weinlandi is a species of frog in the Eleutherodactylidae family endemic to eastern Hispaniola ; it is found in the Dominican Republic and central Haiti .
Cylindraspis is a genus of recently extinct giant tortoises .
Xenobalistes tumidipectoris is a species of triggerfish found in the western central Pacific Ocean .
Potentilla villosa is a species of flowering plant in the rose family , Rosaceae .
Dictyoceratida is an order of sponges in the subclass Ceractinomorpha containing five families .
Callionymus rivatoni is a species of dragonet native to the Pacific Ocean around New Caledonia .
Lirularia acuticostata , common name the sharp - keeled lirularia , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Trochidae , the top snails .
Petersianthus quadrialatus ( also called Toog and Philippine Rosewood ) is a emergent tropical rainforest tree species in the Lecythidaceae family .
Amphizoa sinica is a species of beetle in the Amphizoidae family .
Coenobita brevimanus is a species of land hermit crab native to the east coast of Africa and the south west Pacific Ocean .
The genus name composed of the Greek μέγας ( mega ) , meaning great , pharangos , meaning gully , and ἀσπίς ( aspis ) shield , referencing Big Gully on Kangaroo Island , the only known site where fossils of Megapharanaspis were collected .
Hymenocallis acutifolia is a plant species first described in 1826 with the name Hymenocallis littoralis var . acutifolia .
Orcuttia inaequalis is a rare species of grass known by the common name San Joaquin Valley Orcutt grass .
Clostridium cadaveris is usually considered non - pathogenic ; unlike other species of Clostridium , it does not produce toxins . Clostridium cadaveris is found in soil , water , and is a normal component of the human intestinal tract .
Dendropithecus is an extinct genus of apes native to East Africa between 20 and 15 million years ago .
Lepanthes papillipetala is a species of orchid found from Mexico ( Chiapas ) to El Salvador .
Eopeachella is an extinct genus of trilobites , fossil marine arthropods , with species of probably small size ( largest headshield ( or cephalon ) 1.1 centimetres or 0.43 inches long ) , entire , articulate specimens have not yet been found .
Clarias batu ( sometimes known under the common name Tioman walking catfish ) is a species of clariid catfish .
Gigantodax is a genus of 68 species of black flies distributed along the Andes from Mexico to Tierra del Fuego in Argentina .
Carabus agnatus is a species of black or purple - coloured beetle from Carabidae family , that is can be found in Georgia and Russia .
The Agathidinae are a subfamily of braconid parasitic wasps .
Dissosteira is a genus of grasshoppers in the family Acrididae found in North America .
Crocus versicolor is a species of flowering plant in the genus Crocus of the family Iridaceae , found in southeast France , Monaco , and Northwestern Italy .
The South Georgia shag is one of the blue - eyed shags , sometimes placed in the genera Leucocarbo , and a subspecies of the imperial shag .
The Platystomatidae ( signal flies ) are a distinctive family of flies ( Diptera ) .
The Cuban pewee or crescent - eyed pewee ( Contopus caribaeus ) is a species of bird in the Tyrannidae family .
Sonatsa is a genus of marine , mud - dwelling polychaete worms containing the sole species Sonatsa meridionalis .
Cicadulina mbila , the maize leafhopper , is a leafhopper species in the genus Cicadulina .
Galerina sulciceps is a dangerously toxic species of fungus in the family Strophariaceae , of the order Agaricales .
Mahonia aquifolium ( Oregon - grape or Oregon grape ) is a species of flowering plant in the family Berberidaceae , native to western North America .
Laemanctus is a genus of corytophanid lizards , commonly referred to as conehead lizards or casquehead iguanas , which are endemic to Central America .
Uncaria rhynchophylla ( simplified Chinese : 钓钩藤 ; traditional Chinese : 釣鉤藤 ; pinyin : diào gōu téng ; literally : `` fish hook vine '' ) or the cat 's claw herb is a plant species used in traditional Chinese medicine .
The secretive behavior of Abbott 's duiker , along with its largely nocturnal habits and preference for dense vegetation , means little is known about the ecology and behavior of this species .
Caldilinea aerophila is a species of filamentous thermophilic bacteria , and the type species of its genus .
Euphorbia remyi ( syn . Chamaesyce remyi ) is a rare species of flowering plant in the euphorb family known by the common name Remy 's sandmat .
Stagonosuchus is an extinct genus of rauisuchid rauisuchian .
Downingia montana is a species of flowering plant in the bellflower family known by the common name Sierra calicoflower .
Athous angulifrons is a species of click beetle from Elateridae family that is endemic to Kamnik--
Propilidium reticulatum , common name the reticulate cocculina , is a species of sea snail , a true limpet , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Lepetidae , one of the families of true limpets .
Aglaia spectabilis ( Thai : ตาเสือใหญ่ , Khmer bangkeou damrei ) is a species of tree in the Meliaceae family .
Chaenopsis megalops is a species of chaenopsid blenny found around Colombia , in the western central Atlantic Ocean .
Triviella ovulata , common name `` baby 's toes '' , is a species of small sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusc in the family Triviidae , the trivias .
Eumastacoidea is a superfamily within the order Orthoptera .
Calliostoma formosense , common name the Formosa top shell , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Calliostomatidae .
Betula raddeana is a species of plant in the Betulaceae family .
Calliphora hilli is a blow fly species in the genus Calliphora .
Pseudoniphargus grandimanus is a species of crustacean in family Hadziidae .
Pachydactylus vansoni , commonly known as Van Son 's thick - toed gecko , is a species of gecko , which is endemic to Southern Africa .
Dyckia milagrensis is a plant species of the genus Dyckia , native to Bahia , Brazil .
Zoanthids ( order Zoantharia also called Zoanthidea or Zoanthiniaria ) are an order of cnidarians commonly found in coral reefs , the deep sea and many other marine environments around the world .
Semicassis thomsoni is a species of large predatory sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusc in the family Cassidae , the helmet shells and their allies .
Argemone is a genus of flowering plants in the family Papaveraceae commonly known as prickly poppies .
Draba californica is a species of flowering plant in the mustard family , known as the California draba .
Papilio syfanius is a species of swallowtail butterfly from the genus Papilio that is found in China .
It contains the single species Atelophleps tridesma , which is found in Australia .
Conyza ramosissima ( dwarf horseweed ) is a species of North American plants in the daisy family .
Geranium platypetalum , commonly called glandular crane's - bill or broad - petaled geranium , is a herbaceous plant species in the Geraniaceae family .
Some authors consider Noctua janthe and Noctua janthina to be the same species .
Chaetocladus capitatus is an extinct species of green algae in the genus Chaetocladus , which existed in what is now Cornwallis Island , Arctic Canada , during the Silurian period .
Kinosternoidea is a superfamily of aquatic turtles , which included two families :
The Merulinidae are a family of reef - building stony corals .
Vologdinella is a genus of fossils that , while historically aligned to the cephalopods ( family Volborthellidae ) , has since been removed from this group , The organism bears superficial resemblance to Salterella , although it is now thought to be a dasycladacean alga .
Suriana is a monotypic genus of flowering plants containing only Suriana maritima , which is commonly known as bay cedar .
The Lycoperdales are a now outdated order of fungi .
Hemilytoceras is a lytoceratin ammonite genus with round inner whorls , outer whorls becoming depressed and in some developing high lamellae ( ribs ) that bend forward over the venter .
Periophthalmodon is a genus of mudskippers found along muddy shores , estuaries and lower reaches of rivers in Southeast Asia , Papua New Guinea and Queensland , Australia .
Rhyparella decempunctata is a species of ulidiid or picture - winged fly in the genus Rhyparella of the family Tephritidae .
Pogonopoma parahybae is a species of armored catfish endemic to Brazil where it is found in the Paraíba do Sul river basin , where it occurs in areas of mid to strong water current usually associated with rocky substrate .
Lyonothamnus is a monotypic genus of trees in the rose family containing the single living species Lyonothamnus floribundus , which is known by the common name Catalina ironwood , and the subspecies L. f. ssp .
Bario steindachneri is a species of characin from Brazil and Peru .
Dorcadion pedestre is a species of a longhorn beetle in the Lamiinae subfamily .
Aerides crispa is a species of epiphytic orchid native to western India .
Calliandra elegans is a plant species in the genus Calliandra found in Brazil .
Brachinus plagiatus is a species of ground beetle from the Brachininae subfamily that can be found in Albania , Bulgaria , France , Greece , Hungary , Italy , Moldova , Slovakia , southern part of Russia , all states of former Yugoslavia ( except for Macedonia ) , and in Western Europe .
Oonops hasselti is a spider species found in Scandinavia .
Calochortus nuttallii is a species within the genus Calochortus , in a sub - group generally referred to as Mariposa Lilies .
The genus Helwingia consists of shrubs native to eastern Asia , the Himalayas , and northern Indochina .
Nuxia floribunda ( forest elder , forest nuxia or wild elder ) is a species of tree in the Stilbaceae family , that is native to moist regions of southern Africa , East Africa and central tropical Africa .
Piratula hurkai is a wolf spider species found in Ukraine , Russia , Georgia and Abkhazia .
Pampatheriidae ( `` Pampas beasts '' ) is an extinct family of large plantigrade armored xenarthrans related to Glyptodontidae , an extinct family of much larger and more heavily armored xenarthrans , as well as to smaller extant armadillos ( Dasypodidae ) .
Trisetum fuscum , Tufted bulrush or deer 's hair sedge , is a species of grass in the Poaceae family that is native to North America .
Steindachnerina elegans is a fish species in the genus Steindachnerina found in rivers in Bahia and Minas Gerais , Brazil .
Caristius is a genus of manefishes native to the Atlantic and Pacific oceans .
Acanthemblemaria hastingsi , the Cortez barnacle blenny , is a species of chaenopsid blenny found in the Gulf of California , in the eastern Pacific ocean .
Paraderpas decellei is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , and the only species in the genus Paraderpas .
Plioplatecarpus is a genus of mosasaur lizard .
Abarenicola pacifica or the Pacific lugworm is a large species of polychaete worm found on the west coast of North America and also in Japan .
Rhododendron rubiginosum ( 红棕杜鹃 ) is a rhododendron species native to Myanmar , and Sichuan , Xizang , and Yunnan in China , where it grows at altitudes of 2800 - -3600 meters .
Colius is a bird genus in the family Coliidae .
Amolops himalayanus ( Himalaya sucker frog , Himalaya cascade frog , or Himalaya frog ) is a species of frog found in northeastern India and Nepal .
Alcanivorax pacificus is a species of pyrene - degrading bacteria .
Physalis viscosa is a species of flowering plant in the nightshade family known by many common names , including starhair groundcherry , stellate ground - cherry and grape groundcherry in English , and arrebenta - cavalo , balãozinho , and camambú in Portuguese .
Pravitoceras is an extinct genus of ammonite .
Aborolabis mordax is a species of earwig in the genus Aborolabis , the family Anisolabididae , the suborder Forficulina , and the order Dermaptera .
Dolichoplomelas elongatus is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , and the only species in the genus Dolichoplomelas .
Hemigrammus bleheri is a species of characin found in Amazon Basin in Brazil and Peru .
Sphagnum fallax , the flat - topped bogmoss , is a moss species in the genus Sphagnum
Astragalus albanicus , the Albanian astragalus , is a species of milkvetch that is endemic to the Abşeron and Gobustan districts of Azerbaijan .
Uroplatus phantasticus , the Baweng satanic leaf gecko , is a species of gecko indigenous to the island of Madagascar .
The Himalayan water shrew ( Chimarrogale himalayica ) is a species of mammal in the family Soricidae .
Sphaerodactylus plummeri is a species of Sphaerodactylus , a very small gecko found in the Dominican Republic .
Alinguata is a genus of moth in the Alucitidae family containing only one species Alinguata neblina , which is found in Venezuela .
Gentianopsis is a genus of flowering plants in the gentian family known commonly as fringed gentians .
Papilio oxynius is a species of swallowtail butterfly from the genus Papilio that is found in Cuba .
Galactia smallii is a rare species of flowering plant in the legume family known by the common name Small 's milkpea .
Acer barbinerve is an Asian species of maple found in Korea , eastern Russia , and northeastern China ( Heilongjiang , Jilin , Liaoning ) .
Schiedea kauaiensis is a rare species of flowering plant in the pink family known by the common name Kauai schiedea .
Streptococcus mitior is a species of Streptococcus .
Pteromeris perplana , or the flat cardita , is a species of bivalve mollusc in the family Carditidae .
Cypraea pantherina , common name the panther cowry , is a species of large tropical sea snail , a cowry , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Cypraeidae , the cowries .
Phyllomedusa is a genus of tree frog from Central and South America .
Aborichthys is a genus of stone loaches found in streams of India with one species also found in Myanmar .
Trichopezinae are a subfamily of empidoid flies .
Eooxylides is a genus of butterfly in the family Lycaenidae . The species in this genus are found in the Indomalaya ecozone .
Zygodon gracilis , the slender yokemoss , is a moss species in the genus Zygodon .
Perleidiformes are an extinct order of prehistoric bony fish .
Blaesodactylus boivini ( commonly known as the Madagascar velvet gecko ) is a species of gecko found in northern Madagascar .
Pteralyxia is a genus of plants in family Apocynaceae , first described as a genus in 1895 .
Cicuta maculata is a species of flowering plant in the carrot family known by several common names , including spotted water hemlock , spotted parsley , spotted cowbane , and the suicide root by the Iroquois .
The Pseudogarypidae are a small family of pseudoscorpions .
The lesser night gecko , Nactus coindemirensis , is a species of lizard in the Gekkonidae family .
Labidochromis shiranus is a species of cichlid endemic to Lake Malawi where it is only known to occur along the western coast of the southeastern arm of the lake .
Pteridium esculentum , commonly known as Austral bracken or simply bracken , is a species of the bracken genus native to a number of countries in the Southern Hemisphere .
Argemone mexicana ( Mexican poppy , Mexican prickly poppy , flowering thistle , cardo or cardosanto ) is a species of poppy found in Mexico and now widely naturalized in many parts of the world .
Ornithoglossum is a genus of plants native to southern Africa , some of which are widely cultivated as ornamentals .
Martynia is a monotypic genus in the Martyniaceae consisting of a single species , Martynia annua , commonly known as the cat 's claw , and is endemic to Mexico .
Paphiopedilum glanduliferum is a species of orchid endemic to northwestern New Guinea ( Irian Jaya Coast , Northwestern New Guinea and Indonesia ) .
Ptilinus is a genus of beetle native to the Palearctic ( including Europe ) , the Near East , the Nearctic , the Neotropical and North Africa .
Procambarus fallax is a species of crayfish in the genus Procambarus .
Potamornis is a prehistoric bird genus that dated back to the late Maastrichtian age of the late Cretaceous period .
Stereum sanguinolentum is a species of fungus in the Stereaceae family .
Conus pergrandis , common name the grand cone , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Conidae , the cone snails and their allies .
Cow sharks are a family , the Hexanchidae , of sharks characterized by an additional pair or pairs of gill slits .
Dendrotriton rabbi ( common name : Guatemalan bromeliad salamander ) is a species of salamander in the family Plethodontidae .
Permocalculus is a genus of red algae known from Permian to Cretaceous strata .
Wisteria ( also spelled Wistaria or Wysteria ) is a genus of flowering plants in the pea family , Fabaceae , that includes ten species of woody climbing bines native to the Eastern United States and to China , Korea , and Japan .
Erromenosteus is a genus of extinct , medium - sized brachythoracid arthrodire placoderm from the Late Frasnian of the Kellwasserkalk facies of Late Devonian Bad Wildungen and Bicken , Germany .
Carreramyia is a genus of hoverflies , with only one known species currently .
Extatosoma popa carlbergi is a subspecies of stick insect in the genus Extatosoma .
Centrocoris spiniger is a species of Coreidae family , subfamily Coreinae .
Peperomia caperata ( emerald ripple peperomia ) is a species of flowering plant in the Piperaceae family , native to Brazil .
Marisaurus ( meaning `` Mari lizard '' , for the Mari tribe of Pakistan ) is a genus of titanosaurian sauropod from the Late Cretaceous of Balochistan , western Pakistan .
Nyssa yunnanensis is a species of tree in the Cornaceae family .
Paramugil is a genus of mugilid mullets found in coastal waters , estuaries and rivers in the western Pacific region , ranging from the South China Sea to Australia .
Patasola magdalenae is an extinct species of New World monkey known from a partial subadult mandible from Colombia , which dates to 12.5 - -13.7 million years ago .
The typical falconets , Microhierax , are a genus of bird of prey in the Falconidae family .
Pethia setnai is a species of cyprinid fish native to streams of the Western Ghats , India .
Afropone is an extinct genus of ant in the formicid subfamily Ponerinae , and is currently unplaced in any of the tribes of that subfamily .
Carinotetraodon imitator , commonly known as dwarf Malabar puffer , is a species of pufferfish found in rivers in the Western Ghats of India .
Ziziphus talanai , with common names are balakat , aligamen , and talanai , is a species of tree in the Rhamnaceae family .
Ophrys sphegodes , commonly known as the Early Spider - orchid , is a species of orchid found on alkaline meadows and waste land .
Algoasaurus ( /ælˌɡoʊ.əˈsɔrəs/ ; `` Algoa Bay reptile '' ) is a genus of sauropod dinosaur from the Tithonian - early Valanginian - age Late Jurassic - Early Cretaceous Upper Kirkwood Formation of Cape Province , South Africa .
The conopid genus Stylogaster is a group of unusual flies .
Euodice is a genus of estrildid songbirds that is recognized by some authorities while some include it within the genus Lonchura where it is treated as a subgenus .
Crinotonia is a genus of shrimp containing the two species C. anastasiae and C. attenuatus .
Eucalyptus pilligaensis , commonly known as the Pilliga Grey Box or Narrow leaved Grey Box , is a species of eucalypt native to eastern Australia .
Kryptopterus geminus is a species of catfish belonging to the family Siluridae .
Zebrasoma is a genus of surgeonfishes native to the Indian and Pacific Oceans .
Taonius is a small genus of glass squid .
Githopsis pulchella is a species of flowering plant in the bellflower family known by the common names Sierra bluecup and largeflower bluecup .
The Gireoud 's Brassia ( Brassia gireoudiana ) is a species of orchid .
Nostoceras is an extinct genus of ammonite from the Campanian stage of the Upper Cretaceous , found in the USA , England , central Europe , west Africa , and Madagascar .
The Antillean siskin ( Spinus dominicensis ) is a species of finch in the Fringillidae family .
Psychrobacter proteolyticus is a species of bacterium first isolated from the Antarctic krill Euphausia superba .
Gibbonsia montereyensis , the Crevice kelpfish , is a species of clinid found along the Pacific coast of North America from British Columbia , Canada , to Baja California , Mexico where it prefers areas close to the shore amongst algae .
Salinispora arenicola is an obligate marine actinomycetes bacterium species .
Rhamdia is a genus of three - barbeled catfishes found in Mexico , and Central and South America .
Alyxia squamulosa , commonly known as Alyxia Vine , is a species of shrub in the Apocynaceae family .
Microseris bigelovii is a species of flowering plant in the aster family known by the common name coastal silverpuffs .
Osmorhiza is a genus of perennial herbs , known generally as sweet cicely , sweetcicely , or sweetroot .
Raorchestes anili ( Anil 's bush frog ) is a species of frog in the Rhacophoridae family .
Calochortus ghiesbreghtii is a Mesoamerican species of plants in the lily family .
Gadomus is a genus of rattails in the family Bathygadidae .
Leptotyphlops longicaudus , or the long - tailed thread snake , is a species of snake in the Leptotyphlopidae family .
Hydrolycus is a genus of dogtooth characins from tropical South America .
Conradina grandiflora is a species of flowering plant in the mint family known by the common name largeflower false rosemary , or large - flowered rosemary .
Turneria dahlii is a species of ant in the genus Turneria .
Glaziellaceae is a family of fungi in the order Pezizales that contains the single monotypic genus Glaziella .
Stylogyne is a genus of shrubs and trees in the family Primulaceae .
Amauropsis islandica , common name the Iceland moonsnail , is a species of predatory sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Naticidae , the moon snails .
Cyphononyx optimus is a species of spider hunting wasps in the family Pompilidae .
Oxyjulis californica is a species of wrasse native to the eastern Pacific Ocean along the coasts of California and Baja California .
Allium trachycoleum is a Middle Eastern species of wild onion found in Israel , Palestine , Lebanon , Syria , Jordan , Turkey , and Iraq .
Pachyiulus dentiger is a species of millipede from Julidae family that can be found in Albania and Greece .
Calyptochloa gracillima is a species of grass ( family Poaceae ) and the only species of the genus Calyptochloa .
Frigidoalvania pelagica , common name the carinate alvania , is a species of minute sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk or micromollusk in the family Rissoidae .
Corchorus is a genus of about 40 - -100 species of flowering plants in the family Malvaceae , native to tropical and subtropical regions throughout the world .
Prochoreutis argyrastra is a species of moth of the Choreutidae family .
Melathrix praetextella is a species of snout moth , and the only species in the genus Melathrix .
Fusinus syracusanus , common name Syracusan Spindle Shell , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Fasciolariidae , the spindle snails , the tulip snails and their allies .
Koelga is an extinct genus of prawn in the order Decapoda .
Brachyglenis is a genus in the butterfly family Riodinidae present only in the Neotropical ecozone .
Banksia ser . Dryandra is a series of 94 species of shrub to small tree in the plant genus Banksia .
Xuanhuaceratops is a genus of dinosaur from the Late Jurassic Period ( dated to 167.7 - -161.2 million years ago ) .
Polyommatus is a diverse genus of butterflies . The members ( species ) are found in the Palearctic ecozone .
Macrophthalmus is a genus of crabs which are widespread across the Indo - Pacific .
Rudbeckia hirta , commonly called black - eyed - susan , is a North American species of flowering plants in the sunflower family , native to the Eastern and Central North America and naturalized in the Western part of the continent as well as in China .
Scolomys ucayalensis , also known as the long - nosed scolomys or Ucayali spiny mouse is a nocturnal rodent species from South America .
The African openbill ( Anastomus lamelligerus ) is a species of stork in the Ciconiidae family .
Secernosaurus ( meaning `` severed lizard '' ) is a genus of herbivorous dinosaur .
Eumastacidae are a family of grasshoppers sometimes known as monkey- or matchstick grasshoppers .
Kreodanthus is a small genus of orchids ( family Orchidaceae ) belonging to the subfamily Orchidoideae .
Elegia inconspicuella is a species of snout moth in the genus Elegia .
Mycena rosella , commonly known as the pink bonnet , is a species of mushroom in the Mycenaceae family .
Epistomentis pictus is a species of beetle in the family Buprestidae , the only species in the genus Epistomentis .
Myriotrema endoflavescens is a species of lichen in the family Thelotremataceae .
Elysia lobata is a species of sea slug , a marine gastropod mollusc in the family Plakobranchidae .
Acanthobrama marmid , or the Mesopotamian bream , is a species of freshwater fish in the Cyprinidae family .
Paedophryne swiftorum is a species of frog from Papua New Guinea discovered in 2008 and formally described in January 2012 .
Escobaria sneedii ( syn . Coryphantha sneedii ) is a rare species of cactus known by the common names Sneed 's pincushion cactus and carpet foxtail cactus .
Yasuhikotakia ( Mekong loaches ) is a genus of botiid loaches , many which are popular aquarium fish .
Prosopium is a genus of freshwater whitefishes found in North America and parts of eastern Russia .
Stingless bees , sometimes called stingless honey bees or simply meliponines , are a large group of bees ( about 500 species ) , comprising the tribe Meliponini ( or subtribe Meliponina according to other authors ) .
Ivesia sericoleuca is a species of flowering plant in the rose family known by the common name Plumas mousetail , or Plumas ivesia .
Acromantis satsumensis is a species of praying mantis native to Japan .
Cercocarpus fothergilloides is a Mexican plant species in the rose family .
Ptarmus is a genus of velvetfishes native to the western Indian Ocean .
Phalacrocarpum is a genus of plants in the chamomile tribe within the daisy family , native to the Iberian Peninsula .
Aerenica canescens is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , and the only species in the genus Aerenica .
Coprosma arborea is a species found in New Zealand .
Anopterus is a genus of two species of shrubs or small trees .
Botrychium is a genus of ferns , seedless vascular plants .
Pinnotheres is a genus of crabs , including the pea crab and New Zealand pea crab .
The family Rhynchocinetidae are a group of small , reclusive red - and - white shrimp .
Limonium ramosissimum , Algerian sea lavender , is a species of sea lavender ( Limonium ) native to the Mediterranean region .
Iniistius trivittatus is a species of wrasse currently only known from the Pacific waters off Hong Kong and Taiwan .
Pseudemys is a genus of large , herbivorous , freshwater turtles of the eastern United States and adjacent northeast Mexico .
Polygala intermontana is a species of flowering plant in the milkwort family known by the common name Intermountain milkwort .
Discolampa is a genus of butterfly in the family Lycaenidae . The genus ranges from Sri Lanka to New Guinea .
Taringa pinoi is a species of sea slug , a dorid nudibranch , shell - less marine opisthobranch gastropod mollusks in the family Discodorididae .
Melicope micrococca is a target species for many insects , including butterflies in the family Papilionidae .
Dudleya is a genus of succulent perennials , consisting of about 45 species in southwest North America .
Vexillum amandum , common name : the Amanda mitre , is a species of small sea snail , marine gastropod mollusk in the family Costellariidae , the ribbed miters .
Astelia menziesiana is a species of plant in the Asteliaceae family that is endemic to the state of Hawaii in the United States .
Liubangosaurus is a genus of sauropod dinosaur which lived during the Early Cretaceous in what is now southern China .
Limnephilidae is a family of caddisflies with about 100 genera .
Octopoteuthis deletron is a species of squid in the genus Octopoteuthis of the family Octopoteuthidae .
Vayssierea felis is a species of sea slug , a dorid nudibranch , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Okadaiidae .
Mimela junii is a species of shining leaf chafer belonging to the family Scarabeidae subfamily Rutelinae .
Clarkia lassenensis is a species of wildflower known by the common name Lassen clarkia .
Stemodia durantifolia is a species of flowering plant in the plantain family known by the common names whitewoolly twintip and purple stemodia .
Flaveria bidentis , the coastal plain yellowtops , is a South American plant species of yellowtops within the sunflower family .
Odontoglossum , first named in 1816 by Karl Sigismund Kunth , is a genus of about 100 orchids .
Bromus arizonicus is a species of brome grass known by the common name Arizona brome .
Hackelia bella is a species of flowering plant in the borage family known by the common name greater showy stickseed .
It contains only one species , Catazetema trivialis , which is found in the Democratic Republic of Congo .
Allium oreoprasum is a species of wild onion native to Central Asia .
The Kazbeg birch mouse ( Sicista kazbegica ) is a species of rodent in the family Dipodidae .
Geranium ibericum , commonly called Caucasian crane's - bill or ( in North America ) Iberian geranium or Caucasus geranium , is a herbaceous plant species in the Geraniaceae family .
Rhizodus ( root tooth ) is an extinct genus of rhizodont , a branch of the Sarcopterygii , the bony vertebrate clade that also includes tetrapods .
Branchiosaurus ( Greek for `` gill lizard '' ) is a genus of small , lightly built early prehistoric amphibians .
Viola rotundifolia , common name roundleaf yellow violet , is a plant species of the genus Viola .
Epipactis , or Helleborine , is a genus of terrestrial orchids consisting of approximately 70 species .
The genus Eharius contains the following species :
Microchloa , smallgrass , is a genus of tropical and subtropical plants in the grass family , native to Africa , southern Asia , northern Australia , and the warmer parts of the Western Hemisphere .
Pseudoperonospora cubensis is a species of water mould known for causing downy mildew on cucurbits such as cantaloupe , cucumber , pumpkin , squash and watermelon .
Cylicioscapha is an extinct genus of fossil mollusk , probably a gastropod , a robust - looking euomphalid from the upper Paleozoic of North America .
Lactarius repraesentaneus , commonly known as the northern bearded milkcap , the northern milkcap , or the purple - staining milkcap , is a species of fungus in the Russulaceae family .
Formosania is a genus of gastromyzontid loaches , most of which are endemic to mainland China .
Leptosolena is a genus of plants in the Zingiberaceae .
Brachyphylla is a genus of leaf - nosed bats in the family Phyllostomidae .
Acetobacter is a genus of acetic acid bacteria .
Absidia is a genus of fungi in the family Cunninghamellaceae .
Bruceomyces is a fungal genus in the division Ascomycota , containing the single species Bruceomyces castoris .
Coreoleuciscus splendidus , also known as the swiri or Korean splendid dace , is a species of fish from the cyprinid family endemic to rivers of the Korean peninsula .
Eucalyptus todtiana is a species of tree native to south - western Australia .
Artemisia borealis is an arctic and alpine species plants of the sunflower family .
Gonyleptidae is a neotropical family of harvestmen ( Order Opiliones ) with more than 800 species , the largest in the Suborder Laniatores and the second largest of the Opiiones as a whole .
Aiakas is a genus of eelpouts containing two species .
Petersianthus is a genus of woody plant in the Lecythidaceae family first described as a genus in 1865 under the name Petersia .
Marginella ornata is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Marginellidae , the margin snails .
Crepidodera lamina is a species of flea beetles from Chrysomelidae family that can be found in Benelux , Italy , Spain , Ukraine , Yugoslavian states , Central Europe , and European part of Turkey .
The insect family Corduliidae contains the emerald dragonflies or green - eyed skimmers .
Alloteropsis ( from the Greek allotrios ( `` strange '' ) and opsis ( `` appearance '' ) ) is a genus of Old World plants in the grass family .
Ceanothus cordulatus is a species of shrub in the buckthorn family Rhamnaceae known by the common names mountain whitethorn and whitethorn ceanothus .
Columnea orientandina is a plant species from Ecuador .
Miturgidae is a family of araneomorph spiders , including nearly 160 species in about 33 genera worldwide .
Canthigaster supramacula , known as the West African Sharpnose - puffer , is a species of marine fish in the family Tetraodontidae .
Romulea is a genus of flowering plants in the iris family , first described as a genus in 1772 .
Saraca dives , is a tree species in genus Saraca belonging to the legume family , native to China , Laos , and Vietnam .
Elenchus maorianus is a parasitic insect species in the genus Elenchus found in New Zealand .
The genus is the only member of the family Eotrogulidae and contains one species Eotrogulus fayoli .
Argyrochosma jonesii , with the common name is Jones ' false cloak fern , is a species of fern native to the southwestern United States and northern Mexico .
Cellana radians , common name the golden limpet , is a species of true limpet , a marine gastropod mollusc in the family Nacellidae , which is one of the true limpet families .
Nebria rubripes is a species of ground beetle in the Nebriinae subfamily that can be found in France and Spain .
This is a monotypic genus , containing the single species Australiaena streimannii .
Calandrinia ciliata is a species of flowering plant in the purslane family known by the common names fringed redmaids and red - maids .
Ammorhynchus is an extinct genus of hyperodapedontid rhynchosaur from middle Triassic ( Anisian stage ) deposits of Navajo County , Arizona .
Leptogyra is a genus of sea snails , marine gastropod mollusks in the family Melanodrymiidae , belonging to the clade Neomphalina .
Venustilifer bountyensis is a species of small deep - water sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusc in the family Eulimidae .
Sonneratia hainanensis ( also called Hainan sonneratia ) is a species of plant in the Lythraceae family .
Xyliphius magdalenae is a species of banjo catfish endemic to Colombia where it is found in the Magdalena River basin .
Heteroponera is a genus of ants in the subfamily Heteroponerinae .
Charnia is the genus name given to a frond - like Ediacaran lifeform with segmented , leaf - like ridges branching alternately to the right and left from a zig - zag medial suture ( thus exhibiting glide reflection , or opposite isometry ) .
Gymnoschoenus is a genus of tussock - forming grasses in the Cyperaceae family .
The orange - bellied lizard , Liolaemus pictus , is a species of lizard in the Iguanidae family .
Fuscospora alessandrii ( ruil ) is a species of plant in the family Nothofagaceae , commonly known as the southern beeches .
Liparis hawaiensis , common name Hawai'i widelip orchid , is a species of orchid that is endemic to the Hawaiian Islands .
Arabis aculeolata is a species of flowering plant in the mustard family known by the common name Waldo rockcress .
Rhabdoblennius nitidus , the Barred - chin blenny , is a species of combtooth blenny found in coral reefs in the western Pacific ocean .
Grisebachianthus is a genus of Cuban flowering plants in the sunflower family .
Trachyglanis minutus is a species of loach catfish found in the Ubangi River in the Republic of the Congo and the Democratic Republic of the Congo .
Clavaria zollingeri , commonly known as the violet coral or the magenta coral , is a widely distributed species of fungus .
Knautia is a genus in the family Caprifoliaceae .
Aphalanthus conradti is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , and the only species in the genus Aphalanthus .
Notropis imeldae , the sardinita de Rio Verde , is a species of ray - finned fish in the Cyprinidae family .
In 1988 , because there was already a Salvia species from China named `` Salvia dolichantha '' ( 1934 ) , Gabriel Alziar renamed the plant to the current Salvia whitehousei , in honor of Eula Whitehouse .
Amphiporus lactifloreus is a species of ribbon worm in the phylum Nemertea .
Janthina pallida , also known as the pale janthina , is a species of holoplanktonic sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Janthinidae , the violet snails or purple storm snails .
Megacephala germaini is a species of ground beetle in the subfamily of Carabinae that was described by Chaudoir in 1865 , and can be found in Argentina and Bolivia .
Euphorbia mercurialina ( mercury spurge ) is a species of plant in the spurge family .
Neomphalidae is a family of sea snails or limpets , specifically deep sea hydrothermal vent limpets .
Archaeogastropoda ( also known as Aspidobranchia ) was a taxonomic order of sea snails used in older classifications of gastropods , i.e. snails and slugs .
Allium robinsonii , the Columbia River Onion or Robinson 's onion , is a rare plant species native to the US States of Washington and Oregon , although some studies suggest that the Oregon populations may now be extinct .
Melica penicillaris is a species of grass in the Poaceae family that is endemic to Inner Anatolia , Turkey where it grows in bushy hills , rocky slopes , on limestone and on gullies at the elevation of 1,000 - -1,800 metres ( 3,300 - -5,900 ft ) .
Cernuella virgata , also known as Helicella virgata , common name , the `` vineyard snail '' , is a species of small , air - breathing land snail , a pulmonate gastropod mollusk in the family Hygromiidae , the hairy snails and their allies .
Crapatalus is a genus of southern sandfishes native to the coastal waters of Australia and New Zealand .
Ameles syriensis is a species of praying mantis found in Syria and Turkey .
Prostanthera ovalifolia , known as the oval - leaf mintbush or purple mintbush , is one of about 90 Australian endemic species from the genus Prostanthera .
Conus spectrum , common name the spectre cone , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Conidae , the cone snails and their allies .
Solidago velutina , the threenerve goldenrod or velvety goldenrod , is a plant species native to Mexico and to the western United States .
Hemimyzon khonensis is a species of hillstream loach in the genus Hemimyzon .
Leptodactylus discodactylus ( common name : Vanzolini 's Amazon frog ) is a species of frog in the Leptodactylidae family .
Cardiocrinum cathayanum is a species of Chinese plants in the lily family , with large showy flowers .
Kardiasperma is an extinct genus of flowering plant in the hazelnut family , Betulaceae , containing the single species Kardiasperma parvum .
Lavatera thuringiaca , the garden tree - mallow , is a species of Lavatera native to eastern Europe and southwestern Asia , from southern Germany south to Italy , and east to southern Russia , Kazakhstan , and Turkey .
Dolichognatha is a widespread genus of tropical and subtropical spiders .
Paraclinus fehlmanni is a species of labrisomid blenny only known from the Pacific coast of Ecuador where it is found in tide pools down to depths of 2 metres ( 6.6 ft ) .
Lamida moncusalis , the cashew shoot and blossom webber , is a species of snout moth in the genus Lamida .
The genus is near - endemic to Southern Africa , Sceliages augias exceptionally ranging as far north as the Democratic Republic of Congo .
Boswellia frereana is a species of plant native to northern Somalia where the locals call it `` Dhidin '' or `` Maydi '' ( other spellings include : Meydi , Meyti , Maidi , Maieti , and Mayeti ) or the king of all frankincense .
Tripterygion melanurus is a species of fish in the family Tripterygiidae , the threefin blennies .
Vitex urceolata is a species of plant in the family Verbenaceae .
Eleutherodactylus verrucipes ( Spanish : Rana - chirrionera Orejona ) is a species of frog in the Eleutherodactylidae family .
Cyathula officinalis ( English common names : Cyathula root , Radix Cyathula , Ox Knee , Chinese : Chuan Niu Xi ) , is a species of Cyathula native to the China ( Guizhou , Hebei , Shanxi , Sichuan , Yunnan , Zhejiang ) and Nepal .
Narcissus hispanicus , the Spanish daffodil , or Great daffodil , is a plant species native to France , Spain and Portugal .
Buthus montanus is a scorpion species found in the mountain ranges of southeastern Spain
Liometopum stygium is an extinct species of Miocene ants in the genus Liometopum .
Dendrophylax filiformis is a species of orchid native to Cuba , Hispaniola , Jamaica and Puerto Rico .
Aquilegia elegantula is a species of columbine known by the common name western red columbine .
Nuxia glomerulata is a species of plant in the Stilbaceae family .
Agapanthia asphodeli is a species of beetle in the Cerambycidae family , that can be found in Algeria , Central , Eastern and Western Europe , Tunisia and Turkey .
Pipturus albidus , known as māmaki ( sometimes waimea , for its resemblance to olomea ) in Hawaiian and known as Waimea pipturus in English , is a species of flowering plant in the nettle family , Urticaceae , that is endemic to Hawaiʻi .
Phytolacca pruinosa , ( Levantine Pokeweed ) is a species of plant in the Phytolaccaceae family .
Echinocereus subinermis is a species of flowering plant in the cactus family Cactaceae , native to north , northwestern , and central Mexico .
Neacomys musseri , also known as Musser 's neacomys or Musser 's bristly mouse , is a rodent species from South America .
Nebria arinae is a species of ground beetle in the Nebriinae family that is endemic to Altai region of Russia .
Yueosaurus was first named by Wenjie Zheng , Xingsheng Jin , Masateru Shibata , Yoichi Azuma and Fangming Yu in 2012 and the type species is Yueosaurus tiantaiensis .
Acromyrmex crassispinus is a species of leaf - cutter ant , a New World ant of the subfamily Myrmicinae found in the wild naturally throughout South America , especially in Argentina and Paraguay .
Tubulariidae is a family of hydroid cnidarians .
This is a monotypic genus , containing the single species Bovicornua intricata , described as new to science in 1993 .
Cerapachys coecus is a species of reddish brown army ant found in Sri Lanka .
Phileurus didymus is a species of wood - feeding beetle belonging to the Scarabaeidae family .
Acanthinucella spirata is a species of predatory sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Muricidae , the murex snails or rock snails .
Mesoplodont whales are fifteen species of toothed whale in the genus Mesoplodon , making it the largest genus in the cetacean order .
Allium tubiflorum is a plant species native to China ( Gansu , Hebei , Henan , Hubei , Shaanxi , Shanxi , Sichuan ) at elevations less than 2000 m. Allium tubiflorum is one of the few species of Allium lacking the characteristic onion / garlic scent .
Cnidium monnieri ( L. ) Cusson ex Juss . , Monnier 's snowparsley , is a flowering plant species in the genus Cnidium .
Heterometrus spinifer , the Giant Forest Scorpion or Giant Blue Scorpion , is a species of scorpions belonging to the family Scorpionidae .
Clelia scytalina , commonly known as the Mexican snake eater or zopilota de altura ( highland mussarana ) , is a species of colubrid snake endemic to the New World .
Gibbaranea bituberculata is a species of ' orbweavers ' belonging to the family Araneidae subfamily Araneinae .
Ranularia trilineata , common name : the Three - lined Triton , is a species of predatory sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Ranellidae , the triton snails , triton shells or tritons .
Leea tinctoria is a species of plant in the Leeaceae family .
Arnioceras is an extinct genus of large , evolute , discoidal ammonite from the Lower Jurassic .
Lepiota nirupama is a species of agaric fungus of the genus Lepiota in the order Agaricales .
The giant talking catfish or giant raphael catfish ( Megalodoras uranoscopus ) is a species of thorny catfish that is native to the Amazon Basin in Bolivia , Brazil , Colombia , Ecuador and Peru .
Harpalus salinus klementzae is a subspecies of ground beetle native to Central Asia , where it could be found in such countries as Mongolia , Chinese province of Xinjiang , and Russian autonomous regions such as Buryat Republic , Chita , Irkutsk , and Maritime Province .
Macrobrachium lar is a species of freshwater shrimp found throughout the Indo - West Pacific area , ranging from East Africa through to the Marquesas Islands and was first described in 1798 .
Vasconcellea pulchra is a species of plant in the Caricaceae family .
Caryophyllia smithii , the Devonshire cup coral , is a species of solitary coral in the family Caryophylliidae .
Trinectes is a genus of American soles native to the Americas .
Galium bifolium is a species of flowering plant in the coffee family known by the common names twinleaf bedstraw and low mountain bedstraw .
Eoplectreurys is an extinct monotypic genus of spider from the family Plectreuridae , with a sole species , Eoplectreurys gertschi .
Metacrinus rotundus , the Japanese sea lily , is a marine invertebrate , a species of stalked crinoid in the family Isselicrinidae .
Farlowella nattereri is a species of armored catfish of the family native to Bolivia , Brazil , Colombia , Ecuador , Guyana and Peru .
Lyriothemis acigastra is a species of dragonfly in the family Libellulidae known from India .
Tabanus eggeri is a Mediterranean species of biting horse - fly , found in southern France , Italy , Albania , Croatia , Herzegovina , Bulgaria , Portugal and Morocco .
Disciotis venosa , commonly known as the bleach cup , veiny cup fungus , or the cup morel is a species of fungus in the family Morchellaceae .
Passiflora alata , the winged - stem passion flower , is a species of flowering plant .
Percrocutidae is an extinct family of hyena - like feliform carnivores endemic to Asia , Africa , and Southern Europe from the Miocene through the Pliocene , existing for about 17.41 million years .
Calotropis is a genus of flowering plants in the dogbane family , Apocynaceae , first described as a genus in 1810 .
Niphidium crassifolium commonly known as the graceful fern is a species of fern in the Polypodiaceae family found in Central and South America .
Orthocis juglandis is a species of tree - fungus beetle in Ciidae family which can be found in Austria , Bosnia and Herzegovina , Kosovo , Montenegro , Serbia , and Voivodina .
Platydemus is a genus of large predatory land flatworms , terrestrial planarians in the family Geoplanidae .
Eulima patula ( known commonly as the Largemouth Eulima ) a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Eulimidae .
Hippolais is a genus of tree warbler in the Acrocephalidae family .
Herrera 's mud turtle ( Kinosternon herrerai ) is a species of mud turtle in the family Kinosternidae .
Chalcophaps is a small genus of doves .
Barbeya oleoides is the only species of its family ( Barbeyaceae ) .
Trichopilia suavis is a species of orchid found from Central America to Colombia .
Calycadenia pauciflora is a species of flowering plant in the daisy family known by the common name smallflower western rosinweed .
Comocladia dodonaea , with common names poison ash , and Christmas bush , is a species of tree in the cashew family , Anacardiaceae .
Bouteloua barbata is a species of grass known by the common name six - weeks grama .
Agave vilmoriniana , sometimes misspelled vilmoriana , and popularly known as Octopus agave , is a species of agave endemic to Mexico .
Triturus is a genus of newts comprising the crested and the marbled newts , which are found from Great Britain through most of continental Europe to westernmost Siberia , Anatolia , and the Caspian Sea region .
Regina rigida , commonly known as the crayfish snake , is a species of snake endemic to the southeastern United States .
Ternstroemia subsessilis , the el yunque colorado , is a species of plant in the Pentaphylacaceae family .
Dodekablennos fraseri is a species of combtooth blenny found in the western Indian Ocean , around Réunion and Mauritius .
The name of the species dates back to 1859 , but this is an uncertain figure because of the uncertainty that Mus nitidulus was indeed a separate species from Mus cervicolor .
Amolops mantzorum ( Sichuan torrent frog ) is a species of frog in the Ranidae family .
Eorasaurus is an extinct genus of archosauromorph known from the middle Late Permian ( late Capitanian or early Wuchiapingian age ) of Tatarstan , European Russia .
Viola selkirkii is a species of violet known by the common names Selkirk 's violet and great - spur violet .
Gerlachea australis is a species of Antarctic dragonfish found at depths of from 200 to 670 metres ( 660 to 2,200 ft ) over the Antarctic continental shelf .
Rhododendron liliiflorum ( 百合花杜鹃 ) is a rhododendron species native to Guangxi , Guizhou , Hunan , and southeast Yunnan , China , where it grows at altitudes of 2800 - -4500 meters .
Salvelinus taranetzi , also known as the Taranetz char , is a species of salmonid fish native to Chukotka , Russia .
Chrysothamnus depressus called Long - flowered rabbitbrush , is a North American species of flowering plants in the aster tribe within the sunflower family .
Podisma pedestris is a species of ' short - horned grasshoppers ' belonging to the family Acrididae subfamily Melanoplinae .
Eucobresia nivalis is a species of air - breathing land snail , a terrestrial pulmonate gastropod mollusk in the family Vitrinidae , the glass snails .
Kaiwhekea is an extinct genus of plesiosaur from the Late Cretaceous ( Maastrichtian age ) of what is now New Zealand .
Histomonas meleagridis is species of parasitic protozoan that infects a wide range of birds including chickens , turkeys , peafowl , quail and pheasants , causing blackhead disease , infectious enterohepatitis , or histomoniasis .
Clubiona subtilis is a spider species with Palearctic distibition .
Biomphalaria havanensis , common name the ghost rams - horn , is a species of air - breathing freshwater snail , an aquatic pulmonate gastropod mollusk in the family Planorbidae , the ram 's horn snails .
Ponerorchis is a small genus of Asian terrestrial tuberous orchids included in the orchid family Orchidaceae .
Kibunea minuta is a species of beetle from a family of elateridae in a genus of Kibunea .
Amblysomus is a genus of golden moles ( also `` African golden moles '' and `` South African golden moles '' ) in the golden mole family , Chrysochloridae .
Diaeretiella rapae is a cosmopolitan parasitoid of many species of aphids , but especially the cabbage aphid , Brevicoryne brassicae .
Trifolium microcephalum is a species of clover known by the common names smallhead clover and small - headed clover .
Violales is a botanical name of an order of flowering plants and takes its name from the included family Violaceae .
Porcellana is a genus of decapod crustaceans in the widespread family Porcellanidae , the porcelain crabs , which superficially resemble true crabs .
Julia burni is a species of a sea snail with shell of two separate hinged pieces or valves , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Juliidae .
Ericameria discoidea , called Whitestem goldenbush or sharp - scale goldenweed or Whitestem goldenbush or sharp - scale goldenweed , is a species of flowering shrub in the daisy family known by the common name whitestem goldenbush .
Yushania is a genus of bamboo in the grass family .
The oral sclerite in the Calliphora quadrimaculata is short compared to other species in the same family .
Cleistesiopsis bifaria , the Smaller spreading pogonia , is a terrestrial species of orchid native to the eastern United States , along the Appalachian Mountains from West Virginia to Alabama .
Myrmelachista schumanni , also known as the lemon ant , is a species of ant that is notable for the creation of Devil 's garden .
Calodendrum is a genus of medium - sized evergreen trees comprising two species from Africa .
Ornithonyssus bursa is a species of mite .
Englerodendron is a small genus of legumes that are native to tropical Africa .
Cola boxiana is a species of medium tree in the Malvaceae family .
Juniperus macrocarpa ( large - fruited juniper , syn . J. oxycedrus subsp . macrocarpa ( Sibth . & Sm . ) Ball ) is a species of juniper , native across the northern Mediterranean region from southwestern Spain east to western Turkey and Cyprus , growing on coastal sand dunes from sea level up to 75 m altitude .
Epicrates fordii , known commonly as the Haitian ground boa , is a species of snake in the Boidae family .
Coprinopsis picacea is a species of fungus in the Psathyrellaceae .
Cissus antarctica ( synonym Cissus oblongata ) , called `` kangaroo vine '' , is one of the best known species of the genus Cissus in the family of Vitaceae .
Blechnum novae - zelandiae , commonly known as palm - leaf fern or kiokio , is a species of fern found in New Zealand .
Saxifraga rivularis is a species of saxifrage known by several common names , including highland saxifrage , weak saxifrage , alpine brook saxifrage , and pygmy saxifrage .
Kozakia baliensis is a species of acetic acid bacteria , with type strain Yo-3 T (= NRIC 0488 T = JCM 11301 T = IFO 16664 T = DSM 14400 T ) .
Marginella floccata ( Wooly Marginella ) is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Marginellidae , the margin snails .
Influenza A virus causes influenza in birds and some mammals , and is the only species of influenza virus A. Influenza virus A is a genus of the Orthomyxoviridae family of viruses .
Thrinaxodontidae is an extinct family of cynodonts that includes the genera Thrinaxodon , Nanictosaurus , Nanocynodon , and Novocynodon , and possibly Bolotridon and Platycraniellus .
Papilio inopinatus is a species of swallowtail butterfly from the genus Papilio that is found in Romang , Babar , Damar and Tanimbar .
Uranotaenia moultoni is a species of mosquito in the genus Uranotaenia .
Chinavia aseada is a species of plant bugs belonging to the family Pentatomidae that is endemic to Passo Fundo , Brazil .
Bactrocera dorsalis is a species of tephritid fruit fly that is endemic to Southeast Asia , but has also been introduced to Hawaii , the Mariana Islands and Tahiti .
Succinea antiqua is an extinct species of small , air - breathing land snail , a terrestrial pulmonate gastropod mollusc in the family Succineidae , the amber snails .
Stagmatoptera is a genus consisting of 14 species of mantises in the subfamily Stagmatopterinae .
Cyathea ledermannii is a species of tree fern native to Papua New Guinea and Bougainville Province in the Solomon Islands , where it is common in submontane rain forest at an altitude of 1000 - 3000 m. The trunk of this plant is erect and grows to about 3 m in height .
Abelia spathulata is a species of Abelia in the honeysuckle family .
Cyrtodactylus yangbayensis , also known as the Yangbay Bent - toed Gecko , is a species of gecko found in Khánh Hòa Province , Vietnam .
Citharacanthus livingstoni is a species of New world tarantula in the Theraphosidae family .
Vertigo heldi is a species of minute , air - breathing land snail , a terrestrial pulmonate gastropod mollusk in the family Vertiginidae , the whorl snail .
Its only described species , Diagondas viridiaureus , is found in Brazil .
Miomantis abyssinica is a species of praying mantis in the genus Miomantis in the order Mantodea , native to North Africa .
Thoracosaurus is an extinct genus of gavialoid crocodilian which existed during the Late Cretaceous and early Paleocene .
Spinegesina hiekei is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , and the only species in the genus Spinegesina .
Lupinus croceus is a species of lupine known by the common name saffron - flowered lupine .
Conus cancellatus , common name the cancellate cone , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Conidae , the cone snails and their allies .
Xylodromus concinnus is a species of rove beetle in the Omaliinae subfamily , that can be found everywhere in Europe , the Near East , and Australia .
Idelesaurus is a genus of dicynodont from Late Permian ( Wuchiapingian ) of Russia .
The type species , Yixianosaurus longimanus , was formally named and described by Xu Xing and Wang Xiaolin in 2003 .
Agaronia propatula is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Olividae , the olives .
The Southern African wildcat ( Felis silvestris cafra ) is one of five subspecies of the wildcat , and is native to southern and south - eastern Africa .
Crichtonpelta is a genus of extinct herbivorous ankylosaurid dinosaur from the Cretaceous of China .
Euparkeriidae is a family of small basal archosauromorph carnivores which lived from the Early Triassic to the Middle Triassic ( Anisian ) .
Spatuloricaria is a genus of armored catfishes native to Central and South America .
Zographus oculator , the Orange - eyed Long - horn Beetle , is a species of flat - faced longhorn beetles belonging to the family Cerambycidae .
Cryptococcus aquaticus is a species of Cryptococcus that is found in extreme climates , and has an optimal growth temperature of 9 ° C , but it can grow at temperatures as low as 2 ° C . When plated on agar it produces smooth , butyrous colonies with a cream coloration .
Trichomycterus longibarbatus is a species of pencil catfish endemic to Brazil , where it is only known from a very small area in Espírito Santo near Santa Teresa .
Nebria genei is a species of ground beetle in the Nebriinae subfamily that is endemic to the island of Sardinia .
Magnolia blumei is a species of magnolia that is endemic to Indonesia .
Paratrachysomus huedepohli is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , and the only species in the genus Paratrachysomus .
Marginella liparozona is a species of colorful small sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the Marginellidae family .
Pseudamiops is a genus of cardinalfishes native to the Pacific and Indian oceans .
Arcovomer passarellii ( common name : Passarelli 's frog ) is a species of frog in the Microhylidae family .
Pervushovisaurus is a genus of platypterygiine ichthyosaur from the Late Cretaceous ( Cenomanian , 94 - 100 Ma ) of the Saratov region in western Russia .
Sphenomorphus striatopunctatum is a species of skink endemic to Sri Lanka .
Carijoa riisei , the snowflake coral or branched pipe coral , is a species of soft coral in the family Clavulariidae .
Larix gmelinii , known as Dahurian larch , is a species of larch native to eastern Siberia and adjacent northeastern Mongolia , northeastern China ( Heilongjiang ) and North Korea .
Palaeorhynchus ( meaning `` old snout '' ) is a genus of prehistoric fish from Central and Southeastern Europe that was described by Wagner in 1860 .
Coelophysis kayentakatae is an extinct species of coelophysid dinosaur that lived approximately 196 million years ago during the early part of the Jurassic Period in what is now the southwestern United States .
Parvancorina is a genus of shield - shaped bilaterally symmetrical fossil animal that lived in the late Ediacaran seafloor .
Chalcolepidius limbatus is a species of beetles in the family Elateridae .
Hoppea dichotoma is a plant species in the genus Hoppea .
Nuphar polysepala ( the great yellow pond - lily or wokas ; syn . Nuphar polysepalum orth . err . , Nuphar lutea subsp . polysepala ( Engelm . ) E.O.Beal ) is a species of Nuphar native to western North America .
The sole species is Tripladenia cunninghamii which is native to New South Wales and Queensland in Australia .
Dryopteris erythrosora ( autumn fern , Japanese wood fern , copper shield fern ) is a species of fern in the family Dryopteridaceae , native to east Asia from China and Japan south to the Philippines , growing in light woodland shade on low mountains or hills .
Doris odhneri is a species of sea slug , a dorid nudibranch , a shell - less marine gastropod mollusk in the family Dorididae .
Procambarus bouvieri is a species of crayfish in the genus Procambarus , living in Central America .
Hedera cypria , is a species of Ivy ( genus Hedera ) which is endemic to the island of Cyprus .
The Master 's Cymbidium ( Cymbidium mastersii ) is a species of orchid .
Juniperus foetidissima , with common names foetid juniper or stinking juniper , is a juniper tree species in the Cupressaceae family .
Pantophthalmus is a genus of large , robust flies whose larvae feed in tree roots .
Combretum imberbe ( Leadwood , Afrikaans : Hardekool , Sotho : Mohwelere - tšhipi , Tsonga : Motswiri , Zulu : iMpondondlovu ) is a characteristic and often impressive bushwillow species of the southern Afrotropics .
Antipathes is a genus of coral in the order Antipatharia , composed of black coral so named for its black skeleton .
The Antalya bleak ( Alburnus baliki ) is a species of ray - finned fish in the genus Alburnus .
The Aristobia approximator is a species of beetle in the Longhorn family .
Haliotis iris , common name paua , blackfoot paua or rainbow abalone , is a species of edible sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Haliotidae , the abalones .
The Highland Splitfin ( Hubbsina turneri ) is a species of splitfin endemic to Mexico where it is found in the Lerma River basin .
Aconitum fischeri is a blue colored flowering plant species of the genus Aconitum in the family Ranunculaceae .
Cranoglanis is the only genus of armorhead catfishes .
Liriope spicata is a species of low , herbaceous flowering plants from East Asia .
Carmentina is a genus of sedge moths .
Caladium lindenii is a species of flowering plant in the Araceae family , named after Belgian botanist Jean Jules Linden .
Acrantophis dumerili , commonly known as Dumeril 's boa and the Madagascar ground boa , is a non - venomous boa species found on Madagascar and Reunion Island .

Phoenicobius aratus is a species of medium - sized , air - breathing land snail , a terrestrial pulmonate gastropod mollusk in the family Bradybaenidae .
Muhlenbergia cuspidata is a species of grass known by the common name plains muhly .
Rosa bridgesii is a species of rose known by the common names pygmy rose and Sierran dwarf rose .
Cheroscorpaena tridactyla , the Humpback waspfish , is a species of wasp scorpionfish found only in the Gulf of Papua where it is an inhabitant of coral reefs .
Euprotomus bulla , common name : the Bubble Conch , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Strombidae , the true conchs .
Micropterix elegans is a species of moth belonging to the family Micropterigidae that was described by Stainton in 1867 , and is endemic to Israel .
Pseudomonacanthus is a genus in the filefishes native to the Indian and western Pacific Oceans .
No Clear Lake splittails have been captured since the early 1970s , and the species is presumed to be extinct .
Stenogobius hawaiiensis is a species of goby endemic to the Hawaiian Islands where it can be found in marine , brackish and fresh waters .
The Tipton kangaroo rat ( Dipodomys nitratoides nitratoides ) , is a subspecies of the San Joaquin kangaroo rat , a rodent in the family Heteromyidae .
The Nassariidae , Nassa mud snails ( USA ) , or dog whelks ( UK ) , are a taxonomic family of small to medium - sized sea snails , marine gastropod mollusks in the clade Neogastropoda .
Scadoxus is a genus of African and Arabian plants in the Amaryllis family , subfamily Amaryllidoideae .
Haliplus leechi is a species of Haliplus discovered by Wallis in 1933 .
Bryomorphe is a monotypic genus of flowering plants in the daisy family , Asteraceae , containing the single species Bryomorphe aretioides .
Phenacodus is an extinct genus of mammals from the late Paleocene through middle Eocene , about 55 million years ago .
Maxillaria triloris , the Three - straped Maxillaria , is a species of orchid ranging from northwestern Venezuela to Ecuador .
Leptosia , commonly called wood whites , is a genus of pierid butterflies from the orangetip tribe ( Anthocharini ) .
Picozoa are a phylum of marine unicellular heterotrophic eukaryotes with a size of less than about 3 µm .
The species Lloviu cuevavirus ( /ˈjɔːvjuːˌkwɛvəˈvaɪrəs/ YAW - vew KWE - və - VY - rəs ) is the taxonomic home of a virus that forms filamentous virion , Lloviu virus ( LLOV ) .

Timia komarowii is a species of ulidiid or picture - winged fly in the genus Timia of the family Ulidiidae .

Priocnemis susterai is a large species of Pepsid spider wasp and is , with Priocnemis perturbator and Priocnemis coriacea , one of three similar species of the subgenus Umbripennis found in Great Britain which are characterised by having plentiful erect hair on the face and propodum .

Hickelia is a genus of African bamboo in the grass family .
Proguithera is a genus of thread - legged bug in the Emesinae .
Pseudostomatella erythrocoma is a species of very small sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk or micromollusk in the family Trochidae , the top snails .
Nepenthes tenax ( /nɨˈpɛnθiːz ˈtɛnæks/ ; from Latin : tenax `` tenacious '' ) is a lowland species of tropical pitcher plant native to northern Queensland , Australia .
Oncometopia is a genus of sharpshooters found in North and South America .
Mallotus oppositifolius is a plant species in the genus Mallotus found in Africa and Madagascar .
Atriplex gardneri is a species of flowering plant in the amaranth family known by the common name Gardner 's saltbush .
Indotriplophysa is a genus of stone loaches native to southern and eastern Asia .
Rhynchodoras woodsi is a species of thorny catfish endemic to Ecuador where it is found in the Bobonaza River ( a tributary of the Pastaza River ) of the upper Amazon River drainage .
Planaxidae , common name planaxids or clusterwinks , are a taxonomic family of small and minute sea snails , pantropical marine gastropod molluscs in the superfamily Cerithoidea .
Nyassachromis breviceps is a species of cichlid endemic to Lake Malawi where it is only found in the southern part of the lake .
In 1923 , the material was redescribed by Friedrich von Huene ( 1875 - -1969 ) , who argued that it could not be included within the genus Megalosaurus and created for the Pierson theropod a separate genus , naming the species Erectopus superbus .
Commophila aeneana , the orange conch , is a species of moth of the Tortricidae family .
Kelmayisaurus is an extinct genus of carcharodontosaurid theropod dinosaur from the early Cretaceous .
Megalorhipida dubiosa is a species of moth in the genus Megalorhipida , known from Brazil .
Orcinus citoniensis is an extinct species of dolphin belonging to the family Delphinidae that lived from 2 to 5 million years ago in the Pliocene .
Alycaeus balingensis is a species of land snail with a gill and an operculum , a terrestrial gastropod mollusk in the Cyclophoridae family .
Pierolapithecus catalaunicus is an extinct species of primate which lived about 13 million years ago during the Miocene in what is now Hostalets de Pierola , Catalonia , giving the name to the species .
Lobatus peruvianus , commonly known as the Peruvian conch or the cock 's comb conch , is a species of large sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Strombidae , the true conchs and their allies .
